text:
that grid, tho...”panty portraits” from 
the panty project on exhibition now 
the wash (as it seams) 
january 21 - march 2
@msuunionartgallery @michigan_state_university_ .
the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. participants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. participants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.
.

text:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🔥이 책은 정말 정말 너무 너무 너무 좋았다. 공감 되는 내용도 엄청 많았고 #페미니즘 에 대한 책이면서 만화가 주를 이뤄서 쉽게 이해가 잘 되고 너무 잘 읽히는 책이었다!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
달님(@imlyingonthe_moon ) 추천으로 읽게 됐는데 정말 추천 너무 감쟈합니다🙇🏻‍♀️❣️ 너뮤 좋은 책이었어요!!! 정말 누구에게나 추천하고 싶은 책이라 학교 도서관 같은 데도 들어갔으면 좋겠고 처음 페미니즘을 접하는 사람들에게도 너무 좋을 거 같은 책!!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🔥페미니즘을 알게 된 전,후의 삶과 삶에 대한 태도가 너무 달라졌다. 사실 페미니즘에 대해 그저 알기만 했던 것은 꽤 전이었던 거 같은데 진짜 ‘알아야겠다’, ‘공부해봐야겠다’ 마음 먹은 건 강남역 살인사건 이후였다.
그 사건 이후로 페미니즘에 대해 공부하고 알게 되면서 정말 이때까지 왜 느끼지 못했지? 싶을 정도로 당연하지 말아야하지만 공기처럼 당연했던 차별들이 피부로 느껴졌다.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
✍🏻너무 자연스러워서, 자연인 줄. -p.17
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
그래서 느꼈던 것들 중에 가장 소름 돋았던 것 세가지가 있었다. 첫번째는, 여자 화장실의 무수히 많은 구멍들이 남자 화장실에는 없다는 거. 당연히 나사 구멍이겠지 생각했었는데 사실 몰카 구멍이었다니, 너무 많아서 자연스러워 보였는데 그게 여자 화장실에만 있고 남자 화장실은 구멍 없이 아주 깨끗했다는 게 정말 소름 돋았었다.
두번째로는, 여자인 친구들과 만날 때 누가 성추행 당했다는 말을 하면 열이면 열, ‘나도 이러이러한 거 당했었어.’ 하는 이야기가 나온다는 거.
사람들이 점점 페미니즘을 알게되고, #미투 #metoo 운동이 일어나고 하면서 점점 다들 목소리를 내게 되자 하나 둘 수면 위로 올라 온 이야기들은 아마 온 세상을 덮고도 한참 남을 거 같다.
세번째로, 나도 모르게 언젠가부터 헤어질 때 인사를 “조심히 들어가.”, “들어가서 카톡해.” 로 했다는 거, 여자라는 이유로 “밤 늦게 다니지마.” 라는 소리를 들었다는 거, 혼자 택시를 타는 게 왜 무섭게 느껴질까 등등 일상에서부터 위협 받고 있는 거 같은 느낌이 들었다.
그 외에 너무나도 많고 어딜가나 들을 수 있는 여성 혐오적 발언들, 이 책에도 나오지만 페미니즘을 막 공부하기 시작했을즈음에 정말 티비 프로그램 볼게 없었다. 인생드라마로 생각했던 것들도 더이상 재탕할 수 없었고, 그렇게 좋아하던 무한도전도 볼 수 없었다.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
어떻게 이제야 알았나 싶게 여성이 화장실에 가는 것도, 밤에 돌아다니는 것도, 혼자 택시를 타는 것도, 혼자 사는 자기 집에 혼자 있는 것도 무서워하는 이 사회는 아무리 생각해도 너무 비정상적인 것 같다.
아무리 해도 일상이 위협받지는 않아야지.
그래서 이 책의 마지막 부분이 많이 기억에 남았다.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
평범한 일상을 누릴 수 있는 사회가 될 때까지 #우리는서로의용기 가 되기를!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
✍🏻어쩌면 성차별이란 모르면 보이지 않고, 보이지 않으면 자연스레 학습되는 것이 아닐까요? -p.39
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🔥무엇보다 아래 세대의 아이들에게까지 이 짐을 얹어주지 않기를. 요즘 나오는 화장품 장난감, ‘사회가 만든 성인 여자의 모습’ 처럼 아이들을 만드려는 상품들을 보면 너무 기괴하다.

tweet_full:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🔥이 책은 정말 정말 너무 너무 너무 좋았다. 공감 되는 내용도 엄청 많았고 #페미니즘 에 대한 책이면서 만화가 주를 이뤄서 쉽게 이해가 잘 되고 너무 잘 읽히는 책이었다!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
달님(@imlyingonthe_moon ) 추천으로 읽게 됐는데 정말 추천 너무 감쟈합니다🙇🏻‍♀️❣️ 너뮤 좋은 책이었어요!!! 정말 누구에게나 추천하고 싶은 책이라 학교 도서관 같은 데도 들어갔으면 좋겠고 처음 페미니즘을 접하는 사람들에게도 너무 좋을 거 같은 책!!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🔥페미니즘을 알게 된 전,후의 삶과 삶에 대한 태도가 너무 달라졌다. 사실 페미니즘에 대해 그저 알기만 했던 것은 꽤 전이었던 거 같은데 진짜 ‘알아야겠다’, ‘공부해봐야겠다’ 마음 먹은 건 강남역 살인사건 이후였다.
그 사건 이후로 페미니즘에 대해 공부하고 알게 되면서 정말 이때까지 왜 느끼지 못했지? 싶을 정도로 당연하지 말아야하지만 공기처럼 당연했던 차별들이 피부로 느껴졌다.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
✍🏻너무 자연스러워서, 자연인 줄. -p.17
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
그래서 느꼈던 것들 중에 가장 소름 돋았던 것 세가지가 있었다. 첫번째는, 여자 화장실의 무수히 많은 구멍들이 남자 화장실에는 없다는 거. 당연히 나사 구멍이겠지 생각했었는데 사실 몰카 구멍이었다니, 너무 많아서 자연스러워 보였는데 그게 여자 화장실에만 있고 남자 화장실은 구멍 없이 아주 깨끗했다는 게 정말 소름 돋았었다.

stop_filter_tweet: ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 🔥이 책은 정말 정말 너무 너무 너무 좋았다 . 공감 되는 내용도 엄청 많았고 에 대한 책이면서 만화가 주를 이뤄서 쉽게 이해가 잘 되고 너무 잘 읽히는 책이었다 ! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 달님 ( ) 추천으로 읽게 됐는데 정말 추천 너무 감쟈합니다🙇🏻‍♀️❣️ 너뮤 좋은 책이었어요 ! ! ! 정말 누구에게나 추천하고 싶은 책이라 학교 도서관 같은 데도 들어갔으면 좋겠고 처음 페미니즘을 접하는 사람들에게도 너무 좋을 거 같은 책 ! ! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 🔥페미니즘을 알게 된 전 , 후의 삶과 삶에 대한 태도가 너무 달라졌다 . 사실 페미니즘에 대해 그저 알기만 했던 것은 꽤 전이었던 거 같은데 진짜 ‘ 알아야겠다 ’ , ‘ 공부해봐야겠다 ’ 마음 먹은 건 강남역 살인사건 이후였다 . 그 사건 이후로 페미니즘에 대해 공부하고 알게 되면서 정말 이때까지 왜 느끼지 못했지 ? 싶을 정도로 당연하지 말아야하지만 공기처럼 당연했던 차별들이 피부로 느껴졌다 . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ✍🏻너무 자연스러워서 , 자연인 줄 . -p.17 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 그래서 느꼈던 것들 중에 가장 소름 돋았던 것 세가지가 있었다 . 첫번째는 , 여자 화장실의 무수히 많은 구멍들이 남자 화장실에는 없다는 거 . 당연히 나사 구멍이겠지 생각했었는데 사실 몰카 구멍이었다니 , 너무 많아서 자연스러워 보였는데 그게 여자 화장실에만 있고 남자 화장실은 구멍 없이 아주 깨끗했다는 게 정말 소름 돋았었다 . 두번째로는 , 여자인 친구들과 만날 때 누가 성추행 당했다는 말을 하면 열이면 열 , ‘ 나도 이러이러한 거 당했었어. ’ 하는 이야기가 나온다는 거 . 사람들이 점점 페미니즘을 알게되고 , 운동이 일어나고 하면서 점점 다들 목소리를 내게 되자 하나 둘 수면 위로 올라 온 이야기들은 아마 온 세상을 덮고도 한참 남을 거 같다 . 세번째로 , 나도 모르게 언젠가부터 헤어질 때 인사를 “ 조심히 들어가. ” , “ 들어가서 카톡해. ” 로 했다는 거 , 여자라는 이유로 “ 밤 늦게 다니지마. ” 라는 소리를 들었다는 거 , 혼자 택시를 타는 게 왜 무섭게 느껴질까 등등 일상에서부터 위협 받고 있는 거 같은 느낌이 들었다 . 그 외에 너무나도 많고 어딜가나 들을 수 있는 여성 혐오적 발언들 , 이 책에도 나오지만 페미니즘을 막 공부하기 시작했을즈음에 정말 티비 프로그램 볼게 없었다 . 인생드라마로 생각했던 것들도 더이상 재탕할 수 없었고 , 그렇게 좋아하던 무한도전도 볼 수 없었다 . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 어떻게 이제야 알았나 싶게 여성이 화장실에 가는 것도 , 밤에 돌아다니는 것도 , 혼자 택시를 타는 것도 , 혼자 사는 자기 집에 혼자 있는 것도 무서워하는 이 사회는 아무리 생각해도 너무 비정상적인 것 같다 . 아무리 해도 일상이 위협받지는 않아야지 . 그래서 이 책의 마지막 부분이 많이 기억에 남았다 . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ✍🏻모두가 안전하고 나답게 살 수 있는 보통 날이 올 때까지 함께해요- ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 평범한 일상을 누릴 수 있는 사회가 될 때까지 가 되기를 ! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ✍🏻어쩌면 성차별이란 모르면 보이지 않고 , 보이지 않으면 자연스레 학습되는 것이 아닐까요 ? -p.39 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 🔥무엇보다 아래 세대의 아이들에게까지 이 짐을 얹어주지 않기를 . 요즘 나오는 화장품 장난감 , ‘ 사회가 만든 성인 여자의 모습 ’ 처럼 아이들을 만드려는 상품들을 보면 너무 기괴하다 . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
dzień dobry, 
dziś chciałabym wam powiedzieć o książce, która została okrzyknięta „powieścią epoki #metoo”, przez swoją odważną tematykę i poruszenie bardzo ważnego problemu, a mianowicie - dyskryminacji kobiet. w wielu miejscach na ziemi, kobiety wciąż nie mają wielu praw, są poniżane, dyskryminowane, wykluczone, źle, czy wręcz potwornie traktowane, bite. „vox” to feministyczna dystopia o świecie, którym rządzą mężczyźni, i w którym kobiety mogą wypowiedzieć jedynie 100 słów dziennie. po samym przeczytaniu opisu książki, poczułam frustrującą potrzebę zapoznania się z nią. sytuacja kobiet na świecie nieustannie się zmienia, jednak nie potrafię uwierzyć w to, ile wciąż zła i niesprawiedliwości dzieje się niektórym z nas na świecie. takie książki są bardzo potrzebne. #spreadawareness #feminismbook #vox

text: jacqui orie (pictured) is a domestic worker and an organizer with the national domestic workers alliance. she’s doing important work, and raising awareness about the workplace abuses domestic workers are faced with in the united states. there are more than 2m domestic workers in our country, and only a handful of states guarantee them basic workplace protections. the domestic workers bill of rights passing would ensure that domestic workers are extended: the right to overtime pay when they put in more than 40 hours a week, the protections of the occupational safety and health administration, the ability to form unions, and ability to seek recourse against harassment and discrimination. it also extends new ones, such as the right to meal and rest breaks, paid sick days, advanced notice of scheduling, written agreements, and privacy and other protections for live-in workers. 💥🙌🏽 these reforms are necessary. the omission of domestic worker rights is a legacy of slavery and race-related class discrimination.

.

text:
senior policy advisor for senator angus king wants to hear from mst survivors!!!! we had an interesting meeting yesterday with the office of senator angus king, (i-me). we spoke directly with his senior policy advisor, steve smith. a veteran himself, he seemed to have a deep concern for survivors of military sexual trauma. in fact, after trina mcdonald and myself shared our stories of rape in the military and the difficulties we both had in accessing va mental health care, mr. smith so graciously offered to hear directly from other mst survivors. he acknowledged that mst is not a gender issue rather an abuse of power. 
mr. smith highlighted the many provisions that have already been put in place to protect survivors and ensure that the process of reporting rape was one which is not only safer but also effective. he felt it would help the senator in his decision making about whether or not to vote in favor of the mjia by being better informed of the struggles service members and veterans face.  in fact, during our meeting mr. smith stated that he would personally like to hear directly from “newer survivors”. steve smith 
http://linkedin.com/in/steve-smith-0b644a46
 #passmjia #military #mst #mstsurvivor #survivor #mytruth #endrape #femaleveteran #timeforchange #metoo #metoomilitary #metoomovement #sharemystory

text:
[ my endo story + session giveaway 🎗️ see below, info in comments👇🏼]
.
the pain started in 2007 after a sexual assault. the guilt and shame alone was terrible, but on top of that i started to have a lot of pelvic pain. a visit to the gyno offered me the very vague diagnosis of pelvic inflammatory disease. i took all the antibiotics, but nothing was getting better, only worse. by 2010 i was having trouble walking. every step i took felt like a knife in my left ovary. later that year i was diagnosed with endometriosis via laparoscopy.
.
over the following years i experienced consistent pain with sex, gyno exams, and pelvic floor pt. more often than not, any of those activities might strike me in just the wrong way, resulting in shooting pain running from my vagina to my throat, vividly offering me memories and emotions that i couldn’t quite place, and dissolving in a mess of tears i couldn’t quite understand. it became clear to me then that emotional trauma was a significant contributor to my pain, and that it was somehow stuck “down there.”
.
fast forward through years of medical mismanagement. over time i took myself off hormonal birth control (yes, this is possible), i changed my diet, and began to slowly recognize my patterns of relating with myself and others, both sexually and non.🌱
.
after becoming an acupuncturist i began seeing postpartum women who were in need of emotional recall and pelvic floor reconnection. it reminded me so deeply of my endo trauma. i felt called to do more, and i began to realize that this wasn’t particular to any one diagnosis, but all women. it was therefore an easy choice when the calling came to teach somatic sexuality and embodiment in addition to managing healthcare. i’ve since been in the ever-evolving process of creating and offering a multi-modality approach to allow women to gain the tools to communicate with their bodies and their sexuality, effectively overcoming shame and moving away from pain.💥
.
like all women, my life is littered with memories of having been touched in ways or being coerced  into doing things that made me uncomfortable at best, violated at worst. [cont. in comments 👇🏼]

text: when i’m not doing calligraphy, i work full time as a social worker in special victims unit. i usually explain to people that i’m like b.d. wong from law & order but admittedly less cool. my job is emotionally exhausting and rewarding at the same time, but there are moments that are bright. when i first saw this card made by @jess.mcsweeney for @littlewellpaperco, i bought it and hung it in my office so that victims could see it and feel heard. i’m so grateful because jess ended up giving me two boxes of them. i met with a young girl recently and she expressed worry that her abuser would “get away with it” and she wanted to “make a protest like the me too movement” if that happened. you should know that sexual abuse is a secretive crime and there is often a lack of physical evidence, relying mostly on testimonial evidence at trial—making them difficult to prove #believeher. after doing this for so many years, i am pretty good at keeping my emotions in check but i almost let myself go here. what a strong girl. what a powerful movement that is going on right now. i told her that her young voice is important and she deserves to be heard. i can’t wait to give her one of these cards to write down her feelings. the me too movement is about taking back a stolen power. bam. | photo by @stacy__yeager
name: Shotgunning for Love Letters

text:
los hombres me explican cosas, de rebecca solnit, $460.
.
.
los hombres me explican cosas, de rebecca solnit, es una de las obras que más han conmovido en los últimos años el debate internacional sobre la violencia contra las mujeres. compilado y publicado en inglés por primera vez en 2014, el volumen reúne ensayos sobre las formas de silenciamiento del género femenino, desde el mansplaining hasta la pandemia de femicidios que afecta tanto a oriente como a occidente, y que solnit aborda como demostraciones de distinto grado de una misma enfermedad cultural que se expresa a través del odio a las mujeres. 
anterior a movimientos como ni una menos y #metoo, los hombres me explican cosas es un libro pionero que pone en perspectiva histórica y mundial, entre otras cuestiones, el problema de la credibilidad de las víctimas de violaciones, las luchas por los derechos de las mujeres y los movimientos de concientización y denuncia de los abusos que afectan en todo el mundo a la población femenina, y con ella a la sociedad humana en su conjunto. un libro urgente y necesario, los hombres me explican cosas es a su vez una introducción a la obra sustanciosa de rebecca solnit, y a su pensamiento al mismo tiempo vasto y enfocado, que cautiva por su claridad, su honestidad y su entereza. .
.
#rebeccasolnit #loshombresmeexplicancosas #niunamenos #metoo #ensayos #feminismo @fiordo_editorial

text:
sexism är lika absurd som rasism i guds ögon. sexism förvandlar bokstavligen män och kvinnor till varandras fiender istället för varandras jämlikar, varandras systrar och bröder. 
den skapar artificiella skiljeväggar överallt, och de sliter sönder guds familj.
bibeln säger klart och tydligt att den gudomliga avbilden utgör mänskligheten, oberoende av kön.

jag kan inte vara motståndare till rasism, där människor diskrimineras på grund av någonting de inte rår för - sin hudfärg - och sedan utan att blinka acceptera en sådan skriande orättvisa som andra plågas av på grund av något annat som de inte heller kan rå för - sitt kön.

för att man ska kunna tala om en verklig frigörelse måste den omfatta även kvinnornas situation.

utdrag ur boken ”gud har en dröm” desmond tutu
#godhaveaplan #jesussaves #holybible #godloveseveryone #menandwomen #theholyspirit #metoo

text:
with black history month coming to a close and women’s history month about to begin i thought tarana burke would be today’s ideal feature. 
tarana burke, a ny native and mom of one, became well known for her “#metoo” movement in late 2017 when the allegations of film producer harvey weinstein’s sexual assaults were brought to the public light. 
although many of us were unfamiliar with tarana burke until recently, she has been putting the footwork into helping victims of sexual abuse for decades. her story begins in 1997 when a 13 year old girl confided to her that she had been sexually assaulted. not knowing what to say or even having the courage to say she  too had been sexually assaulted as a child, left tarana feeling very heavy.  she carried that weight for 10 years before deciding to start her organization, just be inc., which is a nonprofit that helps victims of sexual harassment and assault. 
since then, tarana has devoted herself to finding as many resources as possible to help people who are found in this very same situation.  she has built many celebrity relationships along the way and been able to bring awareness and speak on many platforms to promote her metoo movement.  through this movement alone so many have found their voice and been able to speak out on their abuse. tarana burke is changing lives and allowing the abused to learn to live, love and laugh again despite their abuse and we’re here for it!

@taranajaneen we think you are fabulous and you deserve to be featured! 💕
————————————————

text:
let's talk about consent... we've done a couple of episodes that dabble in the topic - we talked to a sex shop owner about kink, to a sex worker about their experiences in the industry, about the #metoo movement and our own experiences in it.
~
there still seems to be a lot of haze around the topic though. consent is permission. consent is not signing all the boxes, giving consent to one thing doesn't have a blanket effect.
~
consent is the most important part of any interaction with another human, especially in sex and it is particularly important in kink. why? because the platform in which kink is built is from trust. the reason those environments and communities are safe are because they are actively participating in conversation and consent.
~
it is a large playing field - and it is supposed to be play. so knowing what people are comfortable with, what is fun for them, but most importantly knowing that the people they are interacting with are listening to them. that if they say their safe word it will be heard. that they are still in control even if being dominated. taking away someone's consent is rape.
~
if you dont feel comfortable asking someone if they consent then you dont get to participate. and you should probably ask yourself why you don't want to confirm consent. a potentially fun situation can quickly turn scary and harmful if both parties aren't on the same page. there is a huge difference between abuse and play and it lays in consent.
~
have i said consent enough? i hope so. whether you want to stick your finger in someone's butt, have them call you a dirty whore, or tie them up... all have completely different connotations depending on whether or not... you got it... each party consents.

text:
friends! are you familiar with white ribbon canada? their mission is to engage men and boys in the prevention of gender-based violence by promoting equity and transforming social norms. they challenge and support men and boys to realize their potential to be part of the solution in ending all forms of gender-based violence.

on may 29th they are doing their annual event in toronto - walk a mile in her shoes. it's a playful opportunity for men to raise awareness in their community about the serious causes, effects and remediations to men's sexualized violence against women. walk a mile in her shoes asks men to literally walk one mile in women's high-heeled shoes.

text:
всем большое привет ребята💕сегодня я решила вам рассказать о своей любимой еде и напитках уже был пост о моей не любимой еде а теперь будет о любимой💕
начнем📍
•••
•••
•••
1)суши,роллы я обожаю роллы и это одно из самых вкусных для меня блюд🍱
•
2)салат я люблю гарниры и мой фаворит из них это салат🥗
•
3)картошка фри)я просто всегда когда в кафе фастфуда беру картошку фри🍟
•
4)безалкогольное мохито мне очень нравиться сочетание вкусов:мяты,лайма,лимона и газировки)это мой самый любимый напиток🍵
•
5)фрукты мне нравятся почти все фрукты)а особенно фруктовый салат и если там просто нарезаны кусочки фруктов без всяких добавок и сахара🍉
•
6)рыба.ну очень сильно люблю рыбу а особенно  нравятся:форель и тунец🐟
•
7)бельгийские вафли я сладкое не очень люблю но все-таки одна вещь мне просто очень нравиться это бельгийские вафли их я пробывала 1 раз в своей жизни но они сразу стали моим фаворитом🥮
•
8)чипсы я ооочень люблю чипсы возможно это и не еда а перекус главное что они мне ну очень нравятся
и, да я досих пор не прекратила их есть🥔
•
9)креветки тут всё понятно🍤
•
10)сыр косичка не люблю сыр но именно косичка мне нравиться🧀
•
•
•
ну и наверное на этом всё)спасибо что всё дочитали я знаю что вам было интересно ну и я с вами прощаюсь всем пока👋

nikol jumse💜

text:
hey i’m liz! #fridayintroductions are in order on fridays duhhhh.

1. i say p.s. before almost every sentence. p.s. it’s reallly annoying i’m sure 😉

2. i’ve been entrepreneurial since i was a wee one. devising my own lemonade stands, with an added bonus of homemade cookies as a package deal is just one of the many things i did so i could go buy sour straws at 7-11. 🍪

3. if you ask me if i want a drink i’m probably going to assume you mean a mixed one. 🍻

4. i’ve been pregnant 5 times and we have two girls. not a fun fact but one i definitely carry with me. 💕

5. ornan used to make fun of me because of how much i read, but now he’s reading too for the first time in like 10 years so 🤷‍♀️ tell me, if you had to choose, would you choose starbucks or peet’s?

text:
sororidad. la palabra que mejor define el feminismo del siglo xxi. y lo hemos conseguido nosotras.
paso a paso vamos logrando pequeñas metas que un día se convertirán en grandes. ya hemos aprendido lo más importante: si tocan a una nos tocan a todas. y unidas somos mucho más fuertes. las distancias se hacen pequeñas y las hermanas surgen en cualquier lugar del mundo. esto sí es una oleada feminista, aunque nos intenten convencer de lo contrario. ¡sigamos caminando juntas!

#toronto // kitchen table conversations with an incredible group of folx on march 8 at apartment 200. all women and feminized folx are welcome to attend. celebrate international women’s day with us. .
.
more details and how to get your complimentary ticket in the link @minibarcanada’s profile (or https://iwd2019toronto.eventbrite.ca) .
.
about kitchen table conversations: "kitchen table conversations can ignite action, create community, solve problems, reduce barriers and start revolutions. women and feminized people have used kitchen table conversations to reclaim their narratives and empower one another, today we are going to do the same. we are bringing together diverse groups of women and non-binary people in the food, beverage and hospitality industry to collaborate, knowledge exchange, network and build bridges to creating real change." - viktoria belle, founder, dandelion initiative .

text:
some days are harder than others. the pain in your chest is heavy, the fog in your mind is thick. leaving your bed to even brush your teeth or shower seems like climbing everest.

we all have these days, breathe, remember you are here. 
you are strong by just being and tomorrow is another day. 
take the time you need and you deserve today... and just breathe.

#abuse #rape #metoo #survivor #iamhere #iamstrong #loveyourself #mentalhealth #anxeity #cbt #ptsd #heal #love #loveyourself #youarehere

text: a public space books advance copies for reviewers/media of #bettehowland have arrived! it is a story that began with aps no. 23, which we now think of as the lost women issue, as it surfaced essential narratives by writers such as kathleen collins and bette howland for a new generation of readers. collins' collected stories were subsequently published by ecco, along with a nonfiction volume, notes from a black woman’s diary, this year, which prompted @nytbooks to say, "the writer and filmmaker kathleen collins died in 1988, at the age of 46 — young, brilliant and, for the most part, unknown. it was a tragic if not entirely unusual fate. what was striking was how instantly her work was embraced after it was rediscovered — like a missing piece somehow anticipated and long yearned for." this highly-collectible issue, published in 2015 and available in our store at apublicspace.org, continues to reverberate into the world, with @andevers, founder of  @secondshelfbooks in london, noting in an interview with @bitchmedia this week, "i started working on the second shelf before #metoo and before trump was elected. the idea for the business came to me not long after i’d visited a book fair in 2015 in new york and noticed the gender inequality in the room, and also from working at a freelance space in the office of a public space while they were putting out an issue on forgotten and overlooked women writers." our relationship with howland's work and her son, jacob, as we traced a line to her from the day that aps founding editor brigid hughes first encountered her book, w-3, @housingworksbks enriched and inspired our own experience in publishing to the extent that a public space books was born. calm sea and prosperous voyage will be published on may 7, and is distributed to bookstores by @publishersgroupwest (as is a public space magazine now!). for all media inquiries, contact @deweynicole @shrevewilliams #bookstagram

text:
남성 페미니스트로 유명했던 남배우 정요한 성범죄 폭로글입니다.

이제껏 무시당했던 수많은 여성들의 목소리 중 한마디만 따라해도 엄청난 존경과 박수를 받았던 남성 페미니스트들을 기억합니다. 
그리고 이 성범죄자를 인생의 동반자라 칭한 여성분도 계십니다. 부디 정신 차리시기 바랍니다. 2차 가해는 여성도 할 수 있습니다. 안희정 부인 민주원과 똑같은 행보를 보이는 것 같네요. 여성들마저 스스로의 관계, 사랑을 위해 같은 여성의 피해에 무관심한 모습이 안타깝고 화가 납니다.

여러분은 만약, 여러분의 아주 가까운 남성이 성범죄자라면
이를 묵인하지 않을 수 있을까요?
한번쯤 고민해보시기 바랍니다.

#남페미 #자남페 #자칭 #남성 #페미니스트 #유튜버 #남함페 #남성과함께하는페미니즘 #성범죄 #미투 #metoo #withyou #4b

text:
there is no better time than now for a production of ntozake shange’s famed choreopoem and award-winning stage play, “for colored girls who have considered suicide/ when the rainbow is enuf”, according to alicia johnson-williams, director.

commonly known as “for colored girls,” the play will be staged at the encore theatre and gallery march 1-3. the performance is a series of 20 separate poems choreographed to music that weaves interconnected stories of love, empowerment, struggle and loss into a complex representation of sisterhood. the cast typically consists of seven, nameless african-american women who are only identified by the colors they are assigned.

johnson-williams talked about the timeliness of the canonical play, which originally opened in the 1970’s by shange, who died last year. “we’re in the crust of the #metoo movement and #timesup but the fact is, time was always up,” said johnson-williams. “this production speaks directly to women and how they’ve coped with these very issues that even today we still encounter and have to deal with as women and in particular as african american females in the united states of america.” johnson-williams said “for colored girls” has always been an iconic production in african american theatre, particularly as it relates to women. the cast includes local artists such as te’shara monique as the lady in purple; erika kellom as the lady in brown; juna givhan as lady in red; phaith “dj chocolate” frazier as lady in blue; lashonda corder as lady in yellow #urbantheater #blacktheatre #blacktheater #blacktheatrematters #blactor #blactors #inspirationalquotes #motivation #graphicdesign #branding #design #theatre #theater  #birminghamalabama #urbantheatre #gospelplay #stagelife #actor #actorslife #talent @justladyshy @djchocolatedotcom @nadiatellismusic @wizdom_wita_z @sassieshanna @jgivhan
name: Encore Theatre and Gallery

johnson-williams talked about the timeliness of the canonical play, which originally opened in the 1970’s by shange, who died last year. “we’re in the crust of the #metoo movement and #timesup but the fact is, time was always up,” said johnson-williams. “this production speaks directly to women and how they’ve coped with these very issues that even today we still encounter and have to deal with as women and in particular as african american females in the united states of america.” johnson-williams said “for colored girls” has always been an iconic production in african american theatre, particularly as it relates to women. the cast includes local artists such as te’shara monique as the lady in purple; erika kellom as the lady in brown; juna givhan as lady in red; phaith “dj chocolate” frazier as lady in blue; lashonda corder as lady in yellow #urbantheater #blacktheatre #blacktheater #blacktheatrematters #blactor #blactors #inspirationalquotes #motivation #graphicdesign #branding #design #theatre #theater  #birminghamalabama #urbantheatre #gospelplay #stagelife #actor #actorslife #talent @justladyshy @djchocolatedotcom @nadiatellismusic @wizdom_wita_z @sassieshanna @jgivhan

this was my real life book club read for february, and it is the first book we have all loved, hands down, without a doubt; it's been our favourite so far.
we had all read, rebecca, in our distant, misty pasts, and it was interesting comparing our thoughts and assumptions about the novel with our thoughts and feelings second time around, and having lived a lot more life.
one of these changes is how much more romantic we thought the novel in our younger days, and how much, much, darker it seems to us now. also, how much more nuance there is in the characters and their relationships, and in what is left unsaid. whereas we rooted for the new mr & mrs de winter all the way in the past, now we were not so sure. while we reviled mrs danvers as the villain of the piece in the past, we now held some sympathy for her. we were also left wondering what kind of love mrs danvers really held for rebecca, and what the narrator's jealousy was really directed at when she thought about rebecca; why she thought more about rebecca's presence than her husband's?
.
rebecca is such a great book for a book club read and discussion. we could have talked all night, but in a couple of hours we covered feminism, the english class system, gender and sexuality, manderley as a character, capital punishment, and the shocking end to the novel, which makes you realise you have to go back to the beginning to grasp the conclusion. brilliant!
.
thanks @remembery_tree_reads  for the #daffersanddaffodils .
.

text: from experiencing assault in dark corridors of the er, to feeling like “the operating room is the locker room,” women in healthcare are now speaking out and demanding safe, equitable workplaces. “i thought, well if it happens in their industry, and they’re uniting with farmworkers and all these other industries… i thought it was weird that these conversations were happening in parallel but not joined,” jessi gold, md, ms, tells @inlauraswords. so she sent a tweet to @timesupnow saying, hey, there are some women doctors i think you need to talk to. and the rest is soon to be history, as time’s up healthcare officially launches on march 1. more on how @timesuphc is taking on sexism in doctors’ offices and hospitals at the link in bio. #timesuphc

text:
phantom lady is a more effective assemblage of noirish elements than my last reviewed film #sodarkthenight . however, any advance is stunted by a whole slew of logic problems and a plot that unfolds with all the dramatic suspense of an assembly guide for an ikea cupboard: you know the basic form it’ll end-up taking, just not how it’s going to get there…

while the supporting players are all doing their best within the constraints of the material, only ella raines is, for me, making the most of what’s on offer. by contrast, both curtis & tone are both lumbered with one-note roles, devoid of opportunities for self-expression. forget the men: this is a movie geared towards a new audience of newly-empowered women, hungry to see their experience reflected in the movies.

ever keen to oblige, hollywood complied: just as it’s doing today, though time will tell if the #metoo movement has longer, stronger roots than those encouraged by a world war…

to read my full review of  #phantomlady  by  #robertsiodmak  visit avvaganda.com/phantom-lady  but my ‘triple word / score’ on a movie that’s yet another fine example of b-movie noir?

#repost @world
______________________
pope francis’ former top financial advisor and the vatican’s economy minister, cardinal george pell, has been found guilty of molesting choir boys more than 20 years ago, making him the highest-ranking roman catholic leader ever found guilty of sexual abuse.
-
the 77-year-old, formally considered the third most powerful man in the vatican, was found guilty of forcing oral sex onto a 13-year-old boy after sunday mass in st. patrick’s cathedral in melbourne in 1996 when he was the city’s archbishop. he was also convicted of an assault in which he grabbed a boy’s genitals.
-
the court heard testimony from one of the victims. the other victim died of a drug overdose in 2014, according to the bbc. sentencing proceedings are beginning on wednesday and are expected to last a few days. pell was found guilty in december, but a judge barred news outlets from publishing anything about the verdict out of concerns it would influence a jury in a second trial for an additional round of assault allegations.
_
the suppression order was only lifted on tuesday after the second trial was canceled. pope francis expelled pell from his group of advisors in december. (📷: getty)

nós mulheres, queremos  exercer nossa feminilidade, sem que isso signifique que tenhamos que aceitar o assédio moral e sexual.
queremos usar batom vermelho, sem que isso nos rotule com adjetivos agressivos. 
queremos ser livres para escolher com quem nos relacionar,  conviver e dialogar. 
queremos usar cores, sem que isso signifique,  que desejamos chamar a atenção da maneira errada.
podemos e devemos dizer não,  ao assédio,  as más intenções e aos abusos.
diga  não, aos que lhe julgam da pior maneira.
participe dessa campanha!

text:
“your fingers entwined with mine, and suddenly life made sense”.
.

the logical thing to do would have been for me to stand there tell the truth & say it's a guy i dated last year but because i felt panicked the words "i don't know who he is, he must be one of my brothers friends" fell out of my mouth quicker than the shit falls out your ass hole after a bad case of diarrhoea. i remember walking into my kitchen thinking "why the fuck have i just done that??" my higher self was floating above my head, tutting with disappointment. i felt sick and i was shaking and i realised that the reason why i lied was because i panicked. i felt like i had done something wrong...even tho i hadn't but that feeling triggered my old survival behaviour because of my experience with domestic violence.
.
new blog post...link in the bio 👆🏻
.

.

text:
ensuring #metoo movement advances diversity in leadership
#
progress has been made in terms of women’s equality and protection over the past 10 years. in fact, it was recently the 10th anniversary of the lilly ledbetter fair pay act, the first bill signed into law by president barack obama in 2009. while there have been significant strides in reducing gender bias, harassment and sexual misconduct, clearly there is still work to be done. the #metoo movement has been an important driver in bringing to light numerous cases of sexual abuse and misconduct. however, it has also had the unintended consequence of causing men to refrain from interacting with women for fear of retaliation. considering that male executives play a key role in advancing women into higher levels of leadership, this fear must be taken seriously because if unaddressed it leads to workplaces where there are fewer opportunities for women’s career advancement and informal coaching. bloomberg recently conducted interviews with more than 30 senior executives that suggest many are startled by the #metoo movement — some for good cause while others succumb to fear and retreat from supporting leadership diversity. this is a huge problem for women, men, the companies they work for and society as a whole. when men shy…

text:
"it took me 30 years to realise this incident sent me on a path of being #overweight. i didn’t want to be attractive to other men because of what this guy felt he could do to me. 
i was in my 20s and was a dental nurse in between permanent jobs, so i went to a temping agency and they told me there was a dentist in purley that needed some help. i went to the first session working with him and he seemed friendly enough and everything was fine. the second day when i went in, he started to be quite jokey and jovial and i didn’t really think anything of it at first. as the morning progressed and we got into the afternoon, i started to realise that there was a thing happening, he was being very flirty and i tried to cool everything down. on the third day, he was really strongly flirting with me and he asked me if i had ever kissed a dentist. i told him i wasn’t interested in kissing a dentist and that i had my own boyfriend at home. in between patients, he cornered me in the surgery and tried to force me to kiss him. i don’t know how i managed it, but i got away and went straight to the toilet and locked myself in. i was really embarrassed; looking back i wonder why was i embarrassed, but i was. 
i decided that i couldn’t stay and didn’t want to go back into that surgery with that man; i felt really uncomfortable. i got my bag and told the receptionist i wasn’t going to work with him anymore. she tried to make me stay as we had patients for the rest of the day, but i left. i then had to drive home and tell my boyfriend why i was home early. he was livid and wanted to go and see the dentist but i stopped him. i rang the agency up and told them not to place young women with him. 
now i am 50 and an old woman, i don’t get this attention anyway and i am really motivated to lose the weight and get myself fit."
#nationaleatingdisordersawarenessweek

read more inspiring stories from real life women over on our website: www.connectedsisters.com/stories

i was in my 20s and was a dental nurse in between permanent jobs, so i went to a temping agency and they told me there was a dentist in purley that needed some help. i went to the first session working with him and he seemed friendly enough and everything was fine. the second day when i went in, he staed to be quite jokey and jovial and i didn’t really think anything of it at first. as the morning progressed and we got into the afternoon, i staed to realise that there was a thing happening, he was being very fliy and i tried to cool everything down. on the third day, he was really strongly fliing with me and he asked me if i had ever kissed a dentist. i told him i wasn’t interested in kissing a dentist and that i had my own boyfriend at home. in between patients, he cornered me in the surgery and tried to force me to kiss him. i don’t know how i managed it, but i got away and went straight to the toilet and locked myself in. i was really embarrassed; looking back i wonder why was i embarrassed, but i was. 
i decided that i couldn’t stay and didn’t want to go back into that surgery with that man; i felt really uncomfoable. i got my bag and told the receptionist i wasn’t going to work with him anymore. she tried to make me stay as we had patients for the rest of the day, but i left. i then had to drive home and tell my boyfriend why i was home early. he was livid and wanted to go and see the dentist but i stopped him. i rang the agency up and told them not to place young women with him. 
now i am 50 and an old woman, i don’t get this attention anyway and i am really motivated to lose the weight and get myself fit."

text:
"hey, come on! i thought you were mature enough to know the difference between maintaining personal and a professional relationship. i'm sure now you're comfortable enough with me to wear your backless white dress in a hotel room. trust me, you'll feel relaxed after our meeting." .

i was numb. i stood still. i had zero idea of what was going around me. i stood there feeling absolutely nothing. .

i still couldn't believe what i read. he had the audacity to say, "ofcourse we have met for work but this is personal." .

i sure did abuse him, replied him harshly, and made it crystal clear about never working with him. however, does that change the fact that someone appreciated your efforts only because they would like to sleep with you? .

how do you react to such a situation? please don't tell me to let it go and move on because this will keep on disturbing me time and again. if you feel like i asked for it or gave him hints, please unfollow me right away. .

when things like sexual harrassment repeat themselves, you still don't figure out how to react, what to do, or how to focus for certain period of time. you feel miserable and you end up doubting yourself. i ended up doubting my capabilities and talent. .

but then someone said, "this world might be a cruel place and you'll face many such assholes in your life. but never doubt on yourself. if you were not this talented, people wouldn't have appreciated your work. it isn't your fault. such people are cowards. this is just a stone in your way to success. kick it, don't stumble upon it. and once you do, emerge like the strong ass woman you are!" .

that must've not changed my life but it did help me. it did make me feel better. this coming from a male friend of mine made me believe that not all men are the same. .

you usually don't know what to say or do when someone shares such stories with you. having said that, the least you can do for them is to make sure you won't repeat the same mistake and stand up for something that's morally wrong. .

it feels good to open up and share this with you all. it feels good to know that i did not give anyone enough power to destroy me and my dreams.

text: we were trying to explain peter sellers to someone who was unfamiliar with his work. then we recalled reading "lolita" years after seeing the film - the james mason, sue lyon one - and were raptured at nabokov's writing. considering that english was not his first language made it doubly impressive. we wanted to tell our friend to read the book and deal with mr. sellers later, but she blurted out, "i hate great books!' 😮 then she explained she meant ones they make you read in school. we were then stymied. it's hard to imagine not wanting to know new things or press the edges of one's mind like some athletes do with their bodies. we just wrote down the pink panther film names and quietly added that if she so much as peeked at the steve martin ones, we would.. well, we didn't know what we'd do, but it would be severe. oh btw. vladimir nabokov was also a respected lepidopterist. can hardly keep up with #demrenaissancecats #prosethatpulverizes #deadmadfunnymen #beingtherethen #impropereducation

text:
¿cómo prefiere viajar las mujeres argentinas?✈️👉🏽un estudio de @eventbrite realizado a más de 6.000 mujeres obtuvo datos muy relevantes sobre cómo nos gusta viajar a nosotras👇🏽
📈el 48% eligió viajar con amigas y el 47% hacerlo con pareja.
📈los destinos de playa para desconectarse son los más elegidos.
📈el 62% viaja una vez al año y el 28% puede hacerlo más de una vez en el mismo ciclo.
📈el 21% prefiere hacerlo sola para conocer otras viajeras y disfrutar de la experiencia viajera.

text:
завтра уже 5.

мике завтра будет 5 мес, надо бы делать новое памятное фото, а я ещё старое не выложила😅бяда то какая.
где брать время? ладно, это уже другая тема. 
одна из любимых развлекух мики - плавать с надувным кругом на шее, и теперь я стала за нее маленьк опасаться.. она отталкивается от днища ванны как мяч, в это время я представляю себя вратарём, не просто, а на чм конечно же, пот стекает от волнения (ладно, не пот, вода, которой любезно побрызгала меня дочь) и вооот, ответственный момент иии я ловлю мяч! то есть дочь😹 да я икер касильяс ёл пал фернандес! в общем, с каждым днём моё материнство становится всё  веселее, а забот и слюней всё больше (не моих).
а чего любят вытворять ваши малыши?😆 пост про 5 мес будет интересней, но это не точно.

text:
😓 всё ещё не можете собраться и начать серьёзно и последовательно добиваться своих целей, например, худеть? 🤕 это не только весенний авитаминоз, недостаток времени, солнца, движения или мотиваци! это не просто стресс!

основная проблема не в стрессе, не в окружении... и не в весне - проблема в голове!

когда слишким многим вещам надо уделить внимание, возможностей мозга просто не хватает на всё! и он просто забывает про диету или ваше желание похудеть. а стресс всего лишь следствие этого. но почему то не у всех мозг слишком слаб для эфективных достижений... вокруг множество примеров целеустремленных и успешных!

неуспешные пытаются подражать успешным в действиях... и терпят очередную неудачу. более продвинутые копируют мысли и убеждения успешных... и тоже проигрывают! отличие успешных от неуспешных ещё глубже!

мозг успешных людей по-другому сортирует их мысли - в буквальном смысле "раскладывает их по пополочкам", а не "раскидывает" по своему внутреннему миру. и вы удивитесь - это заметно даже внешне, например, по движениям ваших глаз! #visiotuning не только поможет выявить ваши индивидуальные алгоритмы подобной работы мозга, но и настроить их более эфективным образом. и вы уже будете не подражать успешным людям, вы станете таким человеком!
.
⚠️ только @visiotuning использует современные научные знания, а не заблуждения из-за которых вы много лет не можете получить или сохранить результаты ваших усилий! пишите заявку на пока ещё бесплатную консультацию в direct или в мессенджеры!

спасибо за like!
❤ 
поделитесь с теми, кому это нужно!
💕

what happens when women speak up against harassment in scientific institutions? this week, we wrote a letter to chancellor zeppos @vanderbiltu showing our support for dr. bethann mclaughlin (@mclneuro on twitter) #metoostem founder, mit disobedience awardee, slayer of the rate my professor chili pepper, advocate for safety in science, teller of uncomfortable truths, and accountability bloodhound. dr. mclaughlin may lose her job on feb 28 - today- absent a last-minute reprieve from vanderbilt university. find out more in our #takeactiontuesday post.

text:
https://amzn.to/2hyfwo0 ❤️ „abgründe“ und „obsession“ aus der serie „flüsternde schatten“ von melia rosta

leserstimmen: "abgründe" flüsternde schatten 1

der erste band von melia rostas neuer biographischer reihe ‚flüsternde schatten‘ verlangt dem leser gleich alles ab. denn der abstieg der jungen nina in die zwangsprostitution ist keine überzogene fantasie, sondern nackte realität – eine realität, die der heutigen gesellschaft vollkommen fremd erscheint, für tausende von frauen in den deutschen großstädten aber allzu realer alltag ist.

dieses buch bietet einblicke in eine szene, die den meisten lesern vollkommen fremd erscheint, und öffnet eine welt, von der man sonst nur einen schwachen schatten erlebt. ********************************************* "obsession" flüsternde schatten 2

scheint es auf den ersten blick so, als habe die junge prostituierte nina in ihrem neuen freund nico endlich einen soliden partner gefunden, so kehren sich die rollen schnell um. schon bald treibt sich nico selbst in die finanzielle abhängigkeit; er betrügt nina, er prügelt sie, wenn sie nicht genug geld bringt – kurz, er wird zu ihrem neuen zuhälter.

diese wahre geschichte zeigt auf allzu reale art, wie die rotlicht-szene ihre bewohnner an sich kettet, wie geld korrumpiert und wie selbst der netteste kerl von nebenan sich von dem goldenen glanz eines feuerzeugs blenden lassen kann.

text:
the world is finally taking note of women taking the lead, becoming masters of their own destinies, building anchors and support systems among themselves and getting involved in championing development in their community. 
this is what african women in leadership organisation is all about. 
today i was on the early morning live interview at the national television station of the republic of cameroon crtv with awlo cameroon vice president mrs. yenwo bertha to talk about this and the coming official launching and inuaguration dinner of awlo cameroon this saturday.

i hope you too are taking note and taking sides 😁

join us on saturday for awlo cameroon official launch at franco hotel by 6pm prompt. @awloint 
our annual african women in leadership conference also comes up on 4th & 5th april in rwanda. register: awlo.org/awlc

text_retweet:
baby boys are executed, just for being born male. the baby girls are raped from 6 months old by humans. yes i mean what i say. forceable impregnation is rape! do not support the meat and diary industry.

#repost from @paulsherman7 by @quicksave.app
・・・
repost by @namastevegan2016_2.0:  reposted from @creepycrueltyfree -  @earthlove777
• • • • •
rp @jessyforthevoiceless 
graphic footage - cows can only produce milk after giving birth, so dairy farms have to constantly forcibly impregnate the cows. 
as a result, many baby calves are born. 
since male calves will never produce milk, they are of no use to a dairy farm. ▪ 
some farms let the calves live for a few months in order to slaughter them for veal.
an analysis shows that it can cost a farmer up to £30 per calf to sell it on for beef or veal, while 'early disposal' costs just £9.
▪ 
as seen, the workers shoot days-old calves in the head, then leave them to bleed in a mass grave. 
the worker doesn’t even make any special effort to shoot the calves in a way that will deliver a quick death. 
in addition, each calf only gets one bullet in order to save costs.
(this footage is from a dairy farm in florida).
but make no mistake, this happens all over the world.
----------------------------------------------------------------------
reposted from @lebanesevegans - just a normal and legal practice under the umbrella of “humane” slaughter. you can stop this by not buying dairy anymore. alternatives are everywhere.
.

text:
dzień dobry :) zastanówcie się przez chwilę nad tym, co zrobiłyby kobiety, gdyby nagle liczba słów, które wypowiadają każdego dnia, uległa drastycznemu ograniczeniu?

feministyczna dystopia o świecie rządzonym przez mężczyzn, w którym kobiety mogą wypowiedzieć tylko 100 słów dziennie. mocna, wzbudzająca emocje książka, ważny głos w epoce ruchu #metoo i w świetle ogólnoświatowych dyskusji o prawach kobiet.

czarna bransoletka zaciśnięta na nadgarstku. cyfrowe znaczki układają się w liczbę 15. liczba wypowiedzianych słów nie może przekroczyć 100, każde kolejne słowo oznacza coraz silniejszy ładunek elektryczny. licznik zresetuje się o północy.

zasady są proste: najlepiej usunąć wszystkie językowe ozdobniki, ograniczyć pytania do tych, na które wystarczy odpowiedzieć „tak” lub „nie”. nie pytać dzieci, jak poszło w szkole. nie rozmawiać z mężem, nie wdawać się w dyskusje. ważyć każde słowo.

neurolingwistka dr jean mcclellan wciąż nie potrafi powiedzieć, jak się znalazła w tej utopistycznej rzeczywistości, gdzie rola wszystkich kobiet została ograniczona do milczącej obecności, do zapewniania rodzinie ciepłego posiłku na stole i czystego lokum. jak do tego doszło? kiedy, dosłownie i w przenośni, kobiety zostały zakute w kajdany?

recenzenci podkreślają, że vox to „kawał dobrej literatury. porusza, skłania do refleksji, inspiruje, rozpala emocje. jest fenomenalna i niebagatelna. to jedna z tych książek, o których chce się opowiedzieć wszystkim dookoła”. @wydawnictwomuza

english-> below . -no te da miedo viajar sola?? no, no me da miedo. 
después de preguntarme de dónde soy a donde quiera que viaje, está es la segunda pregunta más comun cada vez que conozco a alguien.

me siento  segura viajando porque se cómo prevenir y actuar frente a cualquier tipo de situación que vaya en contra de mi integridad como mujer

conozcamos nuestros derechos y hagamolos valer. no hay por qué cohibirnos de cosas por miedos instalados en nosotras
____________________________________
-are you not afraid of traveling alone ?! no, i'm not afraid.

after asking me where i am from wherever i travel, this is the second most common question every time i meet someone.

i feel safe traveling because i know how to prevent and act against any type of situation that is against  my integrity as a woman

let's learn about our rights and make them work. there is no need to restrain ourselves from things due to fears installed in us

text:
when was the last time god closed a door for you and you thanked him? when was the last time that you didn’t get what you wanted; what you thought you needed? did you thank god then?
lately i’ve been faced with a lot of closed doors. a lot of things haven’t worked out as planned or as hoped. a lot of things haven’t been in my favor. i’d walk through one door, only for it to be shut in front of me. all the doors i’ve been trying so eagerly to enter have been closed. i’ve been stuck wondering, “what now?”, “what comes next”?it’s natural to want to ask god why. to be frustrated and upset with him. to have a long list of questions and contemplations. but instead of asking him why, i think we should thank him. thank him for all those closed doors. all those decisions he made for you. thank him for those things that didn’t work out. we don’t always see it right then, but those closed doors means he has something better planned. that wasn’t where you needed to be. those things, that person, that place, they weren’t meant for you.the next time your plan doesn’t work out or you don’t get what you wanted, thank him. remember he closed that door with a purpose and a plan, much, much better.
***

text:
the world is finally taking note of women taking the lead, becoming masters of their own destinies, building anchors and support systems among themselves and getting involved in championing development in their community. 
this is what african women in leadership organisation is all about. 
today i was on the early morning live interview at the national television station of the republic of cameroon crtv with awlo cameroon vice president mrs. yenwo bertha to talk about this and the coming official launching and inuaguration dinner of awlo cameroon this saturday at franco hotel by 6pm.
i hope you too are taking note and taking sides 😁
join us on saturday for awlo cameroon official launch.
our annual african women in leadership conference also comes up on 4th & 5th april in rwanda. register: awlo.org/awlc
- dr. elisha attai @elishaattai awlo founder

text:
video taken inside a day care center in north #stlouis county shows a worker tossing a girl across the room and another injured child with some kind of “nail punctures on the skin,” a police sergeant said wednesday.

police began its investigation of brighter day care and preschool after a 3-year-old girl was taken by ambulance feb. 1 to a hospital with a deep gash on her head. she required seven stitches and later was hospitalized for three days after it became infected, her family’s attorney says.

video shows a worker grabbing the girl by the arm and tossing her across a room, said sgt. kevin smith with the north county police cooperative. as police officers were reviewing the video of that assault, they came across a second victim, smith said.

the second child had puncture wounds to the skin.

the child is “doing pretty well now,” smith said. smith had no additional details on the child or that injury. smith said detectives would be seeking warrants soon.

smith said the workers involved in the two incidents were no longer working with the day care center. “we can assure you the children are no longer in danger,” he said.

the director of the day care center declined to speak to a reporter wednesday, referring all questions to her attorney. he released a statement saying that “providing a quality education in a safe environment is of the utmost importance to our teachers and staff.” the statement said the day care was cooperating with authorities.

the video of the worker tossing the 3-year-old girl was released to the post-dispatch by the family’s attorney, jennifer hansen.

hansen said the worker who grabbed the child filled out an “unintentional injury form” and described the injury this way: “bump her head, when she fall out on carpet.” days after the injury, the girl’s family pressed for more information from the day care center’s director to explain how falling on the carpet could produce such a serious injury, hansen said. the director told the girl’s family that she had video of the room where the injury happened, but that she hadn’t viewed it yet, hansen said.

to learn more visit legalactionnews.com

text:
it's been 4 years now.
this very day, four years ago, i remember. i was there. you were too. we already had a history. but we decided. to keep it aside. to not let it ruin what we had before. little had i known. you had something else on your mind. you weren't what i thought you were. obviously. you never could have. "there i was giving you a second chance. but you stabbed me in the back while shaking my hand." i remember you try to come to me. closer. and closer. i tried to stop you. i wished i was not alive to have experienced that. you touched. not where you were supposed to. i was shook. i trembled. i went blank into a void of much worse flashbacks. i came back to my senses. i couldn't have let it happen again. at least i now knew it was wrong. i pushed you again. with all the force that i had. and believe me, i could have shifted mountains with that rage i had. i kicked you out of my house. and my life. but i can never forget what it felt like. and how disgusted you made me feel since then. every year, today.
.
.
.
|| 8 ||
.
.
.
.

text:
here’s a little timeline from the #metoo movement... what are your opinions of the hashtag? do you think it is a good thing, or has it been overused? let us know in the comments! ☺️ ·  2006: activist tarana burke founds just be inc., and calls her non-profit movement “me too”.
·  21st january 2017: millions participate in the women’s march in washington in support of gender equality & civil rights. the march is believed to be the largest single-day demonstration in u.s. history.
·  5th october 2017: new york times story accusing harvey weinstein of sexually harassing women from his company is published. in the following days, over 100 women make allegations against weinstein.
·  8th october 2017: weinstein fired from his company, the weinstein company.
·  16th october 2017: alyssa milano encourages people to share their stories using the #metoo hashtag, igniting the initial traction for the soon-to-be global movement . ·  october 2017: repercussions of the #metoo movement start to affect many industries; according to an infographic made by vox, “over 200 celebrities, politicians and ceos have been accused for sexual harassment”.
·  november - december 2017: big names including kevin spacey, roy moore, louis c.k., senator al franken, today show’s matt lauer, mario batali and more are claimed against for sexual assault. ·  1st january 2018: times’ up initiative, lead by 300 women in the entertainment industry, is born.
·  january 2018: an alias known as “grace” recalls a murky sexual experience with comedian aziz ansari.
·  30th april 2018: r. kelly “sex cult” exposed,  #muterkelly was born
·  september 2018: more than 20 million people watch dr. christine blaisley ford’s case against brett kavanaugh in front of the senate.

text:
sometimes the answers to our 'whys' are right in front of us.

don't hide your scars.
don't hide your troubles.
don't hide your heartaches.
don't hide your disappointments.

allow those very things you feel make you less be the very things that lead you to more.

find those who cause you to say "me too", connect with them so they know they aren't alone in their hard and make the world a better place.

#harassment101
i think after i exposed my location in xx ,zhejiang people do find me. and recently i met a stranger online in real life just by accident because we have very small proximity. 
i want to let people know that when i post these i meant to make art (alternative storytelling) and demonstrate my freedom of expression. 
it does not mean it’s my interest to literally know and be close to everyone. people cannot go close to me with their own interests and assume i’m easy or am willing to be touched, easily to communicate with. in fact, talk to stranger or people i’m less familiar with, am not curious about are my least interests. it bothers me when people are my ig followers and also are my acquaintances just come to me and think they could do anything to me.
i’d rather position myself a weirdo researcher than a popular star. 
leave me alone. 
別煩我。

text:
consider this!!!!! self-love is one of the most important attributes for success and a key to breaking toxic cycles. it allows us to achieve more and live a healthy life with inner peace. the better you feel about yourself, the more you can accomplish. so, we want the best for our children, therefore, we must instill self-love into them as early as possible. not only does it help them accomplish their goals and dreams, but its a protection for them as well. *********
join me on march 20th at 7pm est (((link in bio))) for my next free webinar where we will discuss not only teaching self-love to our children, but the effects of the generation gap also. one more thing, i'll share my own story of childhood trauma and how i've overcome. everyone who attends will receive a copy of my 30 day breaking toxic cycles journal for free! sign up and share this link with others!!!!!
*********
i can't wait to grow, elevate, and assist you with breaking the cycles that have been holding you back!!!!!!!

welcome to feminist swag gear! we are a clothing brand committed to designing all the things, feminist, women’s rights, female empowerment and the movement of political, economic, personal, and social equality of sexes.
our cool and impactful designs are created, in-house, in our design studio here on the west coast. with our ears on the pulse of today’s culture, we want you to know, we hear you and want to help you express yourself!
we are excited to be on facebook, to become part of a like minded community and to be able to offer our products in easy to navigate, visually awesome shop!
to get started, click shop on the left side menu. you can shop all of our items, or we have grouped similar item together in categories for your convenience. we offer a wide array of styles and colors for each of designs. when you see an item you are interested in, click through the different colors offered and then click the blue tab that says “check out on website”.
this will take you to our website and the item listing you are interested in. scroll your mouse down a bit to the color options, click the one you want, select your size above the color selections and hit “but it now”, add it to your cart and proceed to checkout. standard, rush and super rush delivery is available.
it’s that simple. thanks so much for stopping by and happy shopping!

text:
hello! my new #volg and #blog is out with many #reflective #conversations on the recent #diversity #fauxpas and then some #shoutouts too 🔗 link 👆 in bio shortly 
discussions on the recent #blackface
#controversy 
next, most noteworthy i believe is definitely gillette's, #thebestmencanbe #campaign and the backlash it received on account of calling out on #toxicmasculinity

next,  why is #sexualharassment #policy not #genderneutral

because of #metoo a lot of chatter is around framing sexual harassment #policies focused only on women. however, i have been relentlessly working on a more inclusive agenda i.e. framing policies for sure, but also ensuring they are gender-neutral.

biases oh biases! and ass boss!

i will also talk about #biases in the #workplace. how to deal with them. the need also stems from my own personal experiences as i have come across many hiring managers, leaders and decision-makers to have #narcissistic personalities and an inflated sense of self. heck, i have even worked with a few in the recent past! it's not just difficult to work with this type but also detrimental to one's mental health, well-being, and self-esteem. sometimes a tight slap (figuratively) and a walk-out is just sufficient! no matter what's the prevailing job climate, do not let such egomaniacs disintegrate your dignity.

oracle's sad scene

#oracle was recently accused of underpaying #women , #black and #asian employees. such disclosures are very likely trending in 2019. the classic invalidation of pinning #paygap to market forces isn't going to work now.

the #lens of #exclusion in the bias movie!

my own personal experience in dealing with errant companies. i have faced #exclusion challenges not just as a #diversityrecruiter but also as a candidate. i've been in the starring role in the bias movie myself. believe me, it's frustrating to be perpetually "ignored" almost to a point of feeling invisible despite being the #protagonist :)

text:
hello! my new #volg and #blog is out with many #reflective #conversations on the recent #diversity #fauxpas and then some #shoutouts too 🔗 link 👆 in bio shortly 
discussions on the recent #blackface
#controversy 
next, most noteworthy i believe is definitely gillette's, #thebestmencanbe #campaign and the backlash it received on account of calling out on #toxicmasculinity

next,  why is #sexualharassment #policy not #genderneutral

because of #metoo a lot of chatter is around framing sexual harassment #policies focused only on women. however, i have been relentlessly working on a more inclusive agenda i.e. framing policies for sure, but also ensuring they are gender-neutral.

biases oh biases! and ass boss!

i will also talk about #biases in the #workplace. how to deal with them. the need also stems from my own personal experiences as i have come across many hiring managers, leaders and decision-makers to have #narcissistic personalities and an inflated sense of self. heck, i have even worked with a few in the recent past! it's not just difficult to work with this type but also detrimental to one's mental health, well-being, and self-esteem. sometimes a tight slap (figuratively) and a walk-out is just sufficient! no matter what's the prevailing job climate, do not let such egomaniacs disintegrate your dignity.

oracle's sad scene

#oracle was recently accused of underpaying #women , #black and #asian employees. such disclosures are very likely trending in 2019. the classic invalidation of pinning #paygap to market forces isn't going to work now.

the #lens of #exclusion in the bias movie!

my own personal experience in dealing with errant companies. i have faced #exclusion challenges not just as a #diversityrecruiter but also as a candidate. i've been in the starring role in the bias movie myself. believe me, it's frustrating to be perpetually "ignored" almost to a point of feeling invisible despite being the #protagonist :)

text:
the last two years have seen monumental change both for women in our industry and for wider society led by women in our industry! a turning point in the fight for gender equality and sexual misconduct prevention was the #metoo campaign. the evening of the golden globes saw iconic faces in film and theatre standing in solidarity against sexual misconduct. 
in order to honour this, we are having a golden globes inspired event on international women’s day. the dress code will be black to honour the iconic blackout on the red carpet of the golden globes. 
please come and celebrate the fantastic changes that have been made with, for and by women in our industry. 🥂

#metoo #womensday #internationalwomensday #centralsu

text:
che magnifica esperienza il viaggio verso nord che ci ha offerto i boreali, festival all’insegna della grande cultura nord-europea. abbiamo incontrato grandi autori, ci siamo perduti tra ghiacciai in pericolo e leggende gelide, e siamo tornati a casa un po’ più sognatori. per @lindiependente sono stati al festival manilla telesca, ilaria del boca e stefano peradotto: vi raccontiamo come abbiamo attraversato il nord senza muoverci da milano. 
da bjorn larsson al movimento #metoo svedese, dal climate change al party con musica dal vivo, fino al momento in cui emilia lodigiani, fondatrice della casa editrice, riceve dal re di norvegia il riconoscimento come commendatore all’ordine reale al merito di norvegia. perdetevi con noi nel racconto. tutte le foto sono di alec cani @alecani.
.
.
.

text:
whew chile.

this forthcoming michael jackson documentary is causing disarray in the community! this week, in 1984, mike had officially won 8 grammys. a legend, and icon, michael remains one of the most prolific and admired artists the world has ever seen. but unfortunately, there’s always been unsavory allegations about his lifestyle off the stage. accusations of child molestation looming, threatening to overshadow his legacy.

this sunday, @hbo plans to air a documentary detailing these alleged incidents, and many people simply ain’t havin it. here are some of the issues expressed so far:
1. michael is dead and no longer here to tell his side of the story 
2. the creator of the documentary purposely excluded michael’s family from the film
3. the individuals featured are people who admitted to lying under oath

this doc comes at a time when tensions are high following the #metoo movement and some say this is a plot for folks to capitalize. 
others in the black community feel that only black perpetrators are being held accountable-although our goal should never be to detract from these victims’ stories, some people are asking where the elvis presley documentary is, as he was known to date 15 year old girls openly. 👀

personally, i believe victims. but i gotta say...something about this don’t seem quite right. 
interestingly enough, auntie @oprah will be hosting the documentary after show, and i am hoping she asks the hard hitting questions... thoughts? who plans on tuning in?

text:
sexism in social media discussion
wednesday 6th march, 3.15-4.15pm
muirhead, room 113
.
in recent months, the ability to call out sexism and misogyny on social media has transformed the feminist movement. twitter, facebook, instagram and various other forms of social media have provided a platform for feminists and others to raise awareness and address issues of prejudice against women. hashtags such as the #metoo movement and #everydaysexism are social media based feminist campaigns that aimed to gather examples of everyday experiences of sexism in one space. however, despite the opportunities social media has presented the feminist movement, digital platforms also leave women vulnerable to frequent sexist threats and attacks. how do we prevent online misogyny, and more importantly is social media a positive or negative space for women? 
this discussion is hosted by the edacs feminism group and will be led by final year english and history of art student rozeena.

rsvp on the @edacsbham facebook event or by emailing sophia robertshaw (s.f.robertshaw@bham.ac.uk).

when she found me naked on the hard wood floor… coming to from the paralysis drug - i exasperatedly explained to her what this man she told to take me home - had done to me. her response to my pain? she asked me to make chocolate pancakes for her and my rapist. 
the ‘old me’ obliged, her wish has always been my command. my vagina was on fire for the duration of the walk to whole foods to obtain the ingredients we needed for the brunch i was about to make them both. —

she ended up dating my rapist months down the line. she wanted access to his hampton house / lifestyle.

i found out they were dating - when she got picked up from *debbie*’s mansion on lagorce island. ruby never said anything about dating my rapist. i found out the hard way when he pulled up to debbie’s house minutes after i had. 
he screamed “hey you with the 3 feet of hair” at me in the front yard = and i looked over to see someone’s face i thought i would never see again. what the hell was my rapist doing in miami and how the fuck did he know *debbie*?! without warning - ruby flew through the doors of debbie’s mansion and floated down into his white convertible - and away she went cruising into the sunset with my rapist. debbie explained that ruby had been dating him for months now - without saying one word to me.

this is the same guy who i told her was snorting some white powder from a triangular pile on a mirror while he raped me. she told me that the man never would ever ever do cocaine - she believed him wholeheartedly after he had told her so. i said ruby i saw it with my eyes. she said nope, sorry i don’t believe you.

he wore “8mm style mask”  the entire time that he did whatever he did to my body besides ruining my vagina. the bruise he left on my body was so bad, from my neck down to my ankles that everyone on my risd dorm floor came to gawk at the mere insanity of the size of the bruise. 
they played a guessing game trying to figure out how so much petechiae could exist

text:
you've heard the story before
we see it time and again
women with the courage to speak
threatened by those who pretend

that she's making all this up
she's created some big lie
just to take him down
just to ruin his life

what i don't understand
when there's this pattern that we see
why would she want to speak
when she knows they won't believe

brett kavanaugh, donald trump, dr. luke
they all still walk free
why would it be any different
for the men who hurt you and me? 
multiple women come forward
told they are crazy, insane liars
with deceitful motives
lighting a match, starting a fire

they attack her character
paint her as vindictive
bitches who want to hurt them
when for years it's been unwritten

will there ever be a time
when they will see a consequence
or is she to forever hold her tongue
suppressed by his confidence

she'll keep standing tall
and speaking her truth
one day karma will find him
she'll feel nothing but a bruise

text:
a mood. i’m really thankful for all the encouraging comments and positive vibes being sent my way while i’m in the hospital. i’m taking a shit ton of meds and they seem to be helping a little, but i know this is a long process and i gotta be patient with recovery. the psychiatrist here thinks i should see a trauma specialist once i leave to help with my ptsd, but that requires money and i’m sure i’m gunna be in hella debt once i get discharged so 😂 fuck america’s healthcare system forreal. in better news, everyone here calls me by my preferred name and the hospital even let my friends bring my binder yesterday, so i am much more confident walking around the ward. still wouldn’t mind dying, but life ain’t as bad as it seemed before. sending love to all my fellow survivors and mental health warriors ❤️ dms open always

text: what's the last fear you faced? i have been terrified of the ocean for my entire life. i decided to face my fear and go surfing. it was an absolutely amazing experience and something i am so proud of myself for doing. not only did i surf but caught 2 waves. i have been facing fear after fear because i believe in practicing what i preach and i know that they only way to grow is by being uncomfortable. i stepped into something i was so incredibly scared of and on the other side of that fear i found a new depth to me. it was exhilarating and so fulfilling. plus, i didn't get eaten by a shark! #thinkunbroken

text:
still feeling the aftermath of this amazing weekend!! i’m so lucky to be able to teach my passion- yoga for mental and emotional wellness! ❤️🙏🏽❤️
.
we dove deep into this neurophysiological model of multidimensional care that blended the ancient wisdom of yoga and meditation with modern neuroscience and clinical social work. feeling lots of gratitude for participants who were willing to lean into discomfort and try many different experiential yogic practices. 🙏🏽🙏🏽
.
can’t wait to offer this again!!
i think bridging the gap between yoga and mental health care is so important. as we learn how to offer our clients tools that approach their concerns both from a top-down and bottom-up approach, we can be more impactful and empower them to move towards a life of mind, body, and spiritual health- whatever that is for them. 🧠🧘🏾‍♀️🤸‍♀️✨

nikki's story is one of suppressing pain, anger, and shame for years after she was sexually assaulted. for a long time she went on trying to ignore it, until it came rushing back threatening her own wellbeing, and her relationships with her family, and friends. •
thankfully it was during this time that nikki sought help and learned that it is not time who possesses the healing hands, and what the meaning of forgiveness really is. •
listen to the heartbreaking yet awesome story of a victim who became more than a conquerer and emerged as a victor! •
you learn even more about nikki and her wonderful ministry to women at nikkigodsil.com

hur hävdar man sin rätt att inte bli oönskat berörd av en man som inte vill förstå eller ändra på sig, mycket likt förövaren? vad har jag att sätta emot äldre män som tar sig friheter för att de vet att det inte blir några konsekvenser för dem? hur ska jag som traumatiserad ung kvinna kunna hävda mina rättigheter när samhället nekar mig dem? hur ska jag komma ur mitt undvikande beteende när det motsatta leder till övertramp från andra?
.
problemet går så mycket djupare än min ptsd. kanske kan man som kvinna inte någonsin vara helt otraumatiserad i ett samhälle som upprepat utsätter oss för kränkningar och övergrepp.

text:
usually i post about the astounding places i am experiencing in the different countries i am visiting; however, the people i am meeting and learning from around the world are equally as worthy of the attention. 
i had the pleasure of getting to hear from and speak to this amazing group of women today. mrs. anisha cherian is the founding member of raising our voices- an ngo in india’s coastal kerala state that works to rehabilitate women and children who are victims of sexual violence, as well as raise awareness and education about the issue. sexual violence is a rampant problem in india. every 20 minutes, a woman is raped- and this only accounts for reported incidents. however, these courageous and brilliant women are working to spread the #metoo movement and prevent such atrocities from happening in their beloved nation. 
what strikes me most about these women is that they are just like you and i. when women’s issues started to get published in the media because of social media and the spread of the #metoo movement, these women banded together to have a discussion group about the issues. yet, they didn’t stop there. while it’s easy to talk about the issues occurring around us, it takes courage and strength to take action. in anisha’s words, “we can chose to be blind, or we can act.” so they did just that. now, their organization, raising our voices, works tirelessly to improve the issues of sexual violence and misconduct in kerala and break the social stigma around discussing these issues. 
these women are a great example of how discussion can lead to action, and action can lead to change. so, i challenge you to think twice about the discussions you are having today and how those discussions can spark positive change in the world around you. after all, change has to start somewhere. #sassp19

text:
190216~190228
📗
-존재하는 위력은 반드시 행사된다
-"위력이 존재하나 행사되지 않았다"는 말은 업무상 위력에 의한 간음죄를 만든 목적 자체에 위배되는 말이다
.
-미투은 정당하다. 그러나 시비여부가 완전히 투명할 수는 없다. 가해자도 피해자도 이 사회의 규범에서 완전히 벗어날 수 없기 때문이다
-신자유주의 문화는 여성의 존재를 성 역할로만 환원했던 과거 사회와 달리 여성의 생존 방식의 하나로 여성의 개인화를 허용했다.
-한국 사회에서 필요한 것은 '다른 목소리'지 '가장 올바른 목소리'가 아니다
.
-우리는 이 사회에서 어떤 과정을 통해 적법하고 적절한 젠더로 배치되는가?
-'여성'이 겪는 폭력은 여성이어서가 아니라 여성이어야 해서, 여성으로 환원되면서 발생하는 폭력이 아닌지 재검토해야 한다.
_

text:
#nofilter #mugshot tech billionaire henry nicholas is finally charged with drug trafficking in las vegas. police were called to the encore last august when nicholas’ companion was found unconscious in their suite with a semi-deflated balloon lodged in her mouth, according to the arrest report. nicholas told hotel security that a canister found in the room contained nitrous oxide, also known as laughing gas. a search of the suite turned up heroin, methamphetamine, cocaine and mushrooms, according to the report. “the charges are only allegations and not facts,” said david chesnoff, an attorney for nicholas”dr. nicholas and ms. fargo deny the charges. we plan to file a motion to dismiss the entire matter on a number of grounds, including lack of evidence.”
