text:
a letter to the anxious minds:

there's the leaden limbs and the shaky hands. there's the waterfall of thoughts; the loud hum you've just gotten used to. there's the flinching and the loaded eyes. there's your heart trying to out run you. there's your mind telling you not to believe a word anyone says. there's the pull, like something has been pulled away from you and you need to be held forever to get back to your own body. there's the push, like the world is propelling you forward when all you want to do is curl up. there's the crippling insomnia, the inability to understand that thunder does not mean the sky is going to fall, the childlike mentality you fall into when nobody is there to say 'you're safe here'. there's the straight thoughts, the need for affection, the need for understanding, for curiosity, for oxygen. and then there's you, and if you aren't the bravest thing i don't know what is.

text: 🙌🏼 recorde // a pintora tarsila do amaral (1886-1973) é um dos maiores nomes da primeira fase do movimento modernista no brasil. o seu quadro mais famoso, abaporu (1928) inaugurou o movimento antropofágico nas artes plásticas e agora mais uma obra sua, a lua (1928), ganhou destaque internacional. considerada um marco da pintura antropofágica, a obra foi comprada pelo museu de arte moderna de nova york (moma), por aproximadamente 20 milhões de dólares (74 milhões de reais), convertendo-se na mais cara já vendida de um artista brasileiro, superando vaso de flores, de guignard. em nota, o moma destacou: é a "primeira pintura da mais importante modernista da primeira geração". para admirar hoje.

text: i saw this after leaving an appointment mon morning in the flatiron district. and believe it‘s a sign! no matter how hard & impossible you think things are, i promise & i swear, that if you live an honest, transparent & purposeful life (unfortunately sometimes a most traumatic event delivers your purpose), there is most definitely a powerful force (god, or a beloved parent, or something indescribable) that is making sure, that you make all that’s good, happen on this planet. there is no question my amazing father, may he rip, teddy, is that force. not only have i saw signs in the past 9 months, but signs directly pointing to the fact that wants me to know it‘s him. the 1st sign, the expiration date on my the order of protection against my abusive boyfriend, june 13, 2019. it’s my parents wedding anniversary. on that date over 40 years ago, my mom & dad signed an agreement, a marital contract, that they will be together as a unit, by law, in life. & now up until this very same date, my ex partner & i consented to a legal agreement, that we would stay away from each other in every which way in life. after realizing this, i saw sign after sign that he wants me to be safe & that he wants me to make my life matter. i’m a believer now. #thehalpernproject #creativityforapurpose #metoo #domesticviolence #domesticabuse #domesticviolenceawareness #domesticviolencesurvivor #enddomesticviolence #god #godisgood #pray #life #believe #grateful #purpose #photography #photo #photooftheday #picoftheday #instagram #igers #street #streetart #newyork #newyorkcity #nyc #advertising #ad #marketing #creative

text:
// #itoowasmolested by a father figure :: "sabke saath hota hai"//
.
.
"it longs back to a considerable amount of time. i was a young girl who was simply trying to sleep lying in a bed in presence of a man who was a father figure to me. i was quite dear to him but for the reasons that i am not comfortable with anymore. unaware of his intentions, i thought i am in a protected environment when he slid his hand into my shirt. i felt worse on realising what happened with me there! .
.
 on narrating this episode with my mother, i was exposed to a new side of it where she went through something similar at some point in her life. "sabke saath hota hai", she said. i never saw him again but he left me with a lesson, you are unsafe more here than an environment which you have never seen!" i am certain of being confident enough to stand tall against any similar act of my privacy violation! .
.
tag one friend and pledge to stand against the molestation in 'protected' environment. let us stand against it, together! .
.
from a session in collab with @wdc_mirandahouse. want us to do a session/workshop on your college campus? get in touch! .
.

text: ok so no names, but today my rapist was proven guilty in the supreme court... it’s been nearly two years to prove my innocence. i only post this photo because it has been the first time i’ve felt clean since it happened. it’s all over the newspapers and internet however i actually feel like i can write about it instead of being ashamed and dirty. it shouldn’t be a taboo subject where the victim feels dirty it should be the offender who feels the shame and legally now he is the rapist. i don’t really even know how to post on instagram and and this will be my second hashtag ever in my life so here goes for older women who think they have no voice. #metoo #darwin #iwasvictimized 💕💕💕#imnotscaredanymore

text:
🗣 “tarana burke’s #metoo movement was never intended to just be about celebrities and hollywood, though peeling back layers of oppression and abuse wherever they exist is important. but it’s so much bigger than that."
•
on tuesday, njcasa executive director patricia teffenhart testified in front of the legislative committee investigating the allegations of sexual assault against a staffer in governor murphy's administration.
•
in her 18-page testimony, she raised concerns about how the case was handled and the implications it has for victims of sexual violence in new jersey and beyond.
•
➡️ to hear her full testimony, follow the link in our bio. 
#believesurvivors #supportsurvivors

text:
как разобраться, какой объем подойдет именно вам?
⠀
очень сложно самой себе подобрать объем наращивания, пытаясь примерить его с картинки. а наши мастера делают это на раз.
⠀
вы пришли в студию, обсуждаете с мастером, какую яркость вы любите.
вы не красите ресницы совсем, только иногда — на выход? мастер посоветует вам сделать классику, а может 3d ультратонкими ресницами.
⠀
красите, но как — один-два мазка, и вы готовы? тогда это классика, 2d или 3d ресничками потолще.
⠀
каждое утро вы старательно накладываете 2 - 3 слоя туши, а завершает ваш макияж тени и подводка— попробуйте 3d, 4d ⠀
запутались? искусственные ресницы имеют разные толщины: 0,1; 0,07; 0,05 ;0.03
одно и тоже наращивание разными толщинами  будет выглядеть по разному.
⠀
и объем уже будет подбираться от того насколько пышные реснички вы хотите.
⠀
интересно? ставьте ❤, и мы продолжим рассказывать про тонкости ресничных дел. :)

text: the compilers of scripture knew the pain of exile. empire, corruption, enemy capture, prophecy, standing without and calling for justice are all well-worn themes in the bible. it's even been suggested that the story of the garden of eden depicts the "death" experienced by our ancient ancestors as being cast away from their home. what a powerful symbol for the experience of victims of abuse and assault! they are exposed -- all too young -- to the injustice of the world, the assumptions of order turned to chaos, and the evil inclination of humanity. as things stand, these victim-survivors are most often rejected by their communities and loved ones and experience the death of being banished from the garden. the good news of scripture is that god stands with those who are cast out. god's people explore how god is with them and how to worship god away from the garden, the temple, and the promised land.

text:
oh man, this post is going to be hard for me...i’ve been somewhat covering up my past and finally revealed past secrets last year that lead to a police report, a court room and many sleepless nights. 
the absolute truth is that i was sexually abused throughout a good portion of my childhood and just told my family about it last year. 
it’s been a journey to say the least and within the darkness, i’ve had many of my wildest dreams come true and continued to love, share, grow and overcome. (not perfectly, but i pushed through) 
i was inspired to create a community and platform for women like me who want to evolve and leave the past behind. 
i created the @goldengoddesscommunity to lead fellow survivors to freedom, peace of mind and transformation. 
we have all been through something, and i wanted to do something for those who want better for themselves that has gone through or is currently going through what i’ve experienced. 
there are many projects im working on within ggc and can’t wait to reveal them in the near future ❤️ in the meantime, you can read my full story in the link on the @goldengoddesscommunity page , follow and check out the website. 
when i say tattooing saved my life, i really really mean it. ❤️ mark your calendars for march 14th where prints of these butterfly beauty’s will be on sale for $30 and a portion will go to rainn, the nations largest anti-sexual violence organization. i will be  doing simple butterfly tattoos and also taking donations for rainn. more details will come as the event gets closer ❤️ thank you guys sooo much for your ongoing support and i’m excited to embark on this new journey with y’all ⭐️ #metoo

it’s been a journey to say the least and within the darkness, i’ve had many of my wildest dreams come true and continued to love, share, grow and overcome. (not perfectly, but i pushed through) 
i was inspired to create a community and platform for women like me who want to evolve and leave the past behind. 
i created the @goldengoddesscommunity to lead fellow survivors to freedom, peace of mind and transformation. 
we have all been through something, and i wanted to do something for those who want better for themselves that has gone through or is currently going through what i’ve experienced. 
there are many projects im working on within ggc and can’t wait to reveal them in the near future ❤️ in the meantime, you can read my full story in the link on the @goldengoddesscommunity page , follow and check out the website. 
when i say tattooing saved my life, i really really mean it. ❤️ mark your calendars for march 14th where prints of these butterfly beauty’s will be on sale for $30 and a portion will go to rainn, the nations largest anti-sexual violence organization. i will be  doing simple butterfly tattoos and also taking donations for rainn. more details will come as the event gets closer ❤️ thank you guys sooo much for your ongoing support and i’m excited to embark on this new journey with y’all ⭐️ #metoo

text:
thinking back on the times when people have betrayed, used, manipulated, and abused you is never a pleasant thing...i told a friend that i would provide artwork to accompany an article that she is writing and here it is...and here are some of the thoughts that came to me while taking this photo.

#toxicmasculinity is real. the #metoo movement is real. if you are a person who is uncomfortable with these facts i would encourage you to push aside the defensive #emotions that may rise up within you, (the way that many #victims have had to push aside the memories of their very real experiences) and simply try listening. 
maybe this will help. 
there are tasty mushrooms that grow on this earth. there are also poisonous mushrooms that grow on this earth. the existence of poisonous mushrooms does not mean that all mushrooms will make you sick...many of them are wonderful, delicious, happily enjoyed...but the ones that aren't, those can kill you.  see, there is a fundamental difference between mushrooms and poisonous mushrooms, the same way that there is a fundamental difference between masculinity and toxic masculinity. both can, and absolutely do, #coexist. 
if you think that this is a fad, or phase, or just something that the liberal #media has cooked up...again i encourage you to simply stop, and just listen. listen to the #women (and men) in your lives, young and old, #conservative and #liberal, free-spirited or anxious, wealthy or struggling, tomboy or princess...there is absolutely no doubt in my mind that you will be surprised at how many of them, like me, have stories. pain, ridicule, shame, and pride mean most don't share them, but they still have them, just the same. #metoo

text:
people often see me as strong and there is certainly truth to it. however my nervous system is delicate. i do have a smaller „window of tolerance“ as they call it in trauma therapy that most people do. it’s not something i like and so i often forget about it, overestimate myself and take on situations with a lot of intensity for my nervous system. what happens then is i am overwhelmed, need boundaries and space for myself to regulate my nervous system and if there is not enough space i retreat into my core until intensity has past. needing alot of time after to myself. but if in that time afterwards another trigger happens my nervous system does whatever it does to regulate. it’s bit scary to loose control over my body. my circulation often gets very low and then i get into hardly controllable shaking - the body‘s reaction to get warm and release frozen life force. actually you can see that as a normal reaction in animals after trauma. they do not move at first and then often shake and then move about normal business. 
well, i hardly have had these episodes of ptsd as i live my normal life tuned to my capabilities. often it may underwhelm people if they get to live close with me. however this last episode really made me understand and accept myself more and pour love into that wounded part.  i often overlook it or not feel i want to give much attention to so i am not victimizing myself. but it’s not how it heals and what love wants. i like to learn to accept this part with love yet not be defined or limited by it. that means: i have to stand up more firmly when i need boundaries and at times stretch them gently too. but that has to be initiated from me and not the outside. mmm quite the learning. 
who else is living with ptsd / trauma and what how do you manage intense situations. intense for you is often not even considered intense for someone else. 
love to hear from others. dm me. 
__________________________________________________
#livingwithtrauma #traumaintegration #windowoftolerance #ptsd #livingwithptsd #selfregulation #theartofrevealing #somethingaboutme #vulnerablity #nervoussystem #truth #recovery #metoo

text: #metoo. i am done being ashamed for something that someone else should be ashamed of. on june 2, 2016, i went to my first party and i was raped by eran sherman. in december of 2017, i opened up about it, realizing the damage it had done to me. in december of 2018, i went to the police to report the incident and made my own damage worse, trusting the justice system to patch me back up. yesterday, the justice system failed me and decided not to press charges and prosecute my case. i didn't report for me, i did it for everyone else so no one would have to feel what i've had to feel. i say me too so that somebody else in the future won't have to. and if the government won't let me do that on their platform then i will do it on my own. eran sherman is a rapist. i am not doing this for attention or pity. i am doing this for the girls that might be harmed by him in the future, or who already have been. i hope that someday the perpetrator will be the one bearing the consequences of their actions, not the victim. #metoo.

text:
4.30 am
без мейкапа,в большой m-size толстовке и в 4 часа ночи я захотела танцевать.self-acceptance.
я долго шла к принятию себя.вот люди мне говорят: «арай,ты такая хиппи,всегда настрой на 100 %,весело тебе живется».
и тут я задумываюсь.я ведь не всегда такой была.(и сейчас не такая,не судите людей по инсте,лол)
конечно я всегда любила внимание(ведь в 5.30 года меня забрали с детского сада-со средней группы :d) и отправили в школу-посадив на 1 ряд.мой папа всегда приходил на собрания с высоко поднятой головой,потому что я была отличницей,а уж после 7 класса кажется я автоматом была умницей кек,хоть ею никогда не являлась.
у меня никогда не было некого чувства недооценности,ведь родители делали для меня буквально все.ведь даже если я жила в посёлке городского типа,они меня отправляли в лагерь за границей,давали возможность ходить на какие-то там кружки.конечно сейчас у детей возможностей намного больше,но смотря на те времена,когда мы были ещё в школе,в то время,это все казалось нечто крутым.
но все мы знаем,как это даётся.
принятие себя.скажу пример:я ненавидела свои густые чёрные волосы,маленький рост и там ещё всякое.бывали люди,которые придирались ко мне,демонстрирую пассивно-эмоциональный абюз,при этом являясь якобы «друзьями».
и ещё смешной момент: мне не нравилось быть азиатской внешности.я говорила,лучше бы я родилась европейкой,надоели эти  глаза и чёрные волосы 😂
но теперь.все по другому.
я горжусь собой и хочу пожелать всем,тем кто не принимает себя, и не любит к примеру свою внешность..
просто подойдите к зеркалу и скажите «if i was you,i’d wanna be me too”🤣🤷🏼‍♀️
не забывайте,что вы прекрасны.не важно кто это читает:парень/девушка/мужчина/мать/кот 😅
just.enjoy.yourself💛
ведь ты это ты.просто прими это.
и люби себя.
🖖
p.s i hope my foreign friends will translate this by instagram option,because i don’t wanna text it again on english 😁

text:
while speaking to variety, dennis graham a.k.a drake’s dad gave his thoughts on r-kelly and jussie smollett..his thoughts on r-kelly: “he’s a good friend of mine. i wish him the best. i hate that it’s happening to him. there’s a reason why women come out after the fact. he has my support 100%,” just as graham contemplates the reasoning behind why victims of sexual abuse come forward, we contemplate why dennis graham, is a thing at all? 
but don’t color us surprised that his thoughts lean this way, this is a person who has insinuated that women endure abuse by putting themselves in certain situations saying: “but there is something i want to say to these young ladies that allow themselves to go and be in a man’s room or whatever. stop going to these hotels.” & “take your ass home. don't go into a man's room.” (tmz) he further stated (in the past): when tmz presses, asking if there are two sides to blame, he vehemently says no. “no there’s not two sides to blame. you take your ass home,” he said. “don’t go where you might think a man is going to have anything to do with raping you or anything else.” umm why are publications like variety interviewing someone like this over his (not newsworthy) single?? because he’s drake’s dad? when you know better do better, we can’t allow mouthpieces’ like these get ahold of a mic…we don’t know if he’s committed abuse in the past himself but he’s certainly an abuser sympathizer

text:
"a deeper sense of being" series 31 of 44.

become a patron and get exclusive access to poetry videos for just $5/month!

www.patreon.com/unjuliwrites

a deeper sense of being

her mouth speaks rainbows
and her lips
have the faint trace
of humility and grace. 
her hair is
waves of austerity
rooted in
the consciousness 
of her intricate mind. 
delve deeply 
into her soul
and you will find
a brave lion
triumphantly basking
in the aftermath
of a chase
that she has 
won fairly. 
she is there. 
right there
where she belongs. 
freedom is
her middle name
and this is her version 
of the game
of life. 
ask her twice
why she still
delicately 
plants seeds 
into buckets of forgiveness 
and she will tell you
that there is
an abundance of hope
which never dies. 
fortune lays around
her bare feet
and her toes
greet each new step
with a healthy dose
of mindful compassion. 
there is less stress
then there ever has been,
since the birth
of her new way of living
conquered 
the pent-up energy
which was keeping her down. 
you might be astounded
to discover
that her heart doesn't beat;
it pounds ferociously 
because her will
is so strong
it can shatter 
any unwelcome thought
with the sleight
of a finger. 
imagine what she can do
with her hands. 
look into her
candlelit eyes
and you will see
a version of yourself
you never thought
you'd see:
a tree so dense 
that rain 
never reaches the ground
with roots tucked 
under folds of 
cement barriers
reaching all the way
to middle-earth.

point to her
curvy lines 
and you will find
a sequence
of verses
which soothes minds
with the ease
of a simple
raindrop. 
she is a forest
with fires and rivers

text:
so honored to be a part of this film, and to help carry out the vision of gabi faye levin...to draw attention to the #metoo movement & to take survivors of sexual assault seriously.
this film initially started out with the name #metoo, but was influenced by my dirty girl gardening bus, which was a prominent feature in the film...the name organically changing into dirty girl as the process went on.
i play the bus driver, and also featured are one of my current employees & a past employee as survivors of assault, along with many other women (some professional actors) that i had not met before filming.

last night, a short clip of the film's trailer played on multiple screens in times square, nyc!! #dirtygirlgardening #dirtygirlthefilm #metoo #dirtygirl #womeninfilm #gabifayeproductions #timessquare #movietrailer #womenfilmmakers #dirtygirlbus #sexualassault #speakout #survivors #believesurvivors #timesup #yadone #gabifaye #womenmakemovies #believewomen #womensreality #iamanastywoman #empowerwomen
@gabifaye

text:
there are several theories as to how yamaguchi maho came about to be ambushed and assaulted at her dormitory.

firstly, in a now deleted tweet, yamaguchi maho mentioned that her address and private information had been leaked by some members.

secondly, according to a ngt48 management statement, an unnamed member provided information on maho.

thirdly, according to shuukan bunshun (a japanese weekly magazine), the assaulters have been living across maho’s unit for a year and a half.

now, 2ch netizens are speculating that the first leak of ngt48 members’ dormitory address may have started from temporary staff at ngt48 theater to inaoka. inaoka is a well-known ngt48 wota (someone who is a fan of idols or idol groups) as well as speculated to be an idol hunter.

an idol hunter is someone who uses any method that would allow them to enter the innermost sphere of the idol, and causes discomfort or damage to related persons. (see definition of idol hunter:
http://qqpy.tumblr.com/post/182174943121/what-makes-an-idol-hunter-a-blog-about-distance)

from inaoka’s deleted tweets, internet sleuths found that he claimed to have sold personal information of idols to tabloids, boasted about stalking idols to their residences, and that he has had s*x with idols.

text:
join us next wednesday, march 6th from 6-8pm for: visible voices: celebrating the unedited feminist story craft night! @ artisan’s asylum

this is a community workshop by in her words diary in partnership with the somerville arts council & the somerville commission for women
✨
✨
✨
about the project: this collaboration with the somerville arts council and in her words diary photographer, emily falcigno, formed in the spirit of the #metoo movement and the women’s march with the desire to amplify marginalized voices. in honor of women’s history month in march, the inside-out gallery will showcase a variety of experiences and provoke thoughtful conversation around everyday feminism.

bring your friends, family, co-workers; because in these times of change, we need all voices to lift up the invisible and become indivisible. we encourage men, trans, non-binary folks to participate too!

link: https://bit.ly/2tguz2t & in bio!

text:
hello! my name is emily and i want to get to know you! 👉🏼 #introductions

we’re so much more than just a picture on each other’s screens and i’d love to learn something new about you.

here’s a little about me:
i live in texas.
i love watermelon 🍉 bubble gum and black licorice.🤷‍♀️
i have a twin sister and we talk almost every day. 🙎🏼‍♀️🙎🏻‍♀️
i love the mountains and dream of one day living closer to them. 🏔
i have had more surgeries than you can count on two hands. 🏥 
as an adult i’ve learned to sail and wakeboard. ⛵️⚓️
i grew up in minnesota. 
i didn’t used to like to travel #homebody but my husband has since taught me the beauty that can be found in it. ✈️
i love bike rides in the spring time. 🚲

take a second and tell me something about you in the comments.

let’s make this little corner of the internet a place where we can connect and lift each other! 🙌🏻🙌🏻

@apontecichelle te acepto con cada pliegue y capa de piel

te valoro con cada cicatris, estría,  celulitis o cualquier otra marca de vida

te libero de tener que cumplir con las expectativas, parametros y estereotipos  sociales y morales

te respeto por ser mi vehículo para transitar la vida

te amaré aun con todos los cambios que vendrán con el paso del tiempo, la edad y las experiencias

te cuidaré desde cada celula interna a cada poro externo

te protégere de heridas y de cualquier comentario mal intencionado de otro o de mi misma

te pido perdón por cada vez que te agredi, te compare y menos precie

te agradezco por la oportunidad de sentir la vida todos los días

text:
a open form on masculinity for the modern man

hit link in bio for details march 2th sold out

sponsored by remi martin @woodylovell 
the barbershop club is a barbershop that is recognize to be the safe haven for manhood. masculinity is ingrained in the philosophy, while male grooming stands side-by-side with the commandments of being a gentleman , you can rest a sure that with over thousands of conversations had with man from all walks of life we are here to make the world a better place one haircut at a time. join us for and open form aimed at men and their unique challenges and interests. we explore all things manly — from the serious and philosophical to the practical and fun. we seek to uncover how to live with grandpa’s swagger, virtue, and know-how in the present age by wedding the best of the past to the best of the present. showcasing experts on the art of masculinity.  the end goal is to create a synergy of tradition and modernity that offers men a way forward and signposts on how to live an excellent, flourishing life.
ultimately, the the barbershop club aims to encourage our men to be better husbands, fathers, brothers, citizens — a new generation of great men.

dedicated to uncovering the lost art of being a man.

regrooming masculinity unleashes the power of the barbershop to re-imagine men’s gender identities and foster their diversity. by challenging stereotypes about men and masculinity, we investigate how men construct their identities through appearance and how the barbershop can be a vital tool to advance social change. this feminist-driven project creates a new approach to understand and transform how men see themselves, interact with each other, and engage with women.

#maleconsulant #mindset #fatherhood #metoo #manstuff #brotherhood #masculinity #manhood #bespoke #mentoring #vulnerability #selflove #therapy #barbershoptalk #masculine #commandments #gentlemansclub #realtalk #mentalhealth #bussinessman #sportman #thewealthybarber @midcenturyla @prorasousa @hotelnormandie @cassellshamburgers @thenormandieclub @helms

text:
whilst i was recovering and trying to put my life back together piece by piece, i was told by a lot of people (professionals included) i needed to forgive the person(s) who had put me through the pain.

i understand this is a big part of the healing process for many but for me, personally, i have and won’t ever forgive. i use and channel my anger instead for good purposes. 
i am involved and help run a charity which teaches children what legal consent is. i have used the pain and anger to run a half marathon and get fit. most importantly i use my experiences to heal and better myself and i will qualify as a solicitor and master of law later this year. 
i want to do a lot more to help others as i get stronger with the qualifications i have achieved. 
remember it is your healing journey and you need to do what’s right for you. don’t let anyone tell you what you should or should not be feeling, follow your own path and be your own guide 😘

#survivor #fighter #metoo #heal #mentalhealth #roadtorecovery #warrior #keepgoing #nevergiveup  #onedayatatime #loveyourself #rememberwhoyouare #anxeity #ptsd #cbt #mentalhealthawareness #mentalillness

i am involved and help run a charity which teaches children what legal consent is. i have used the pain and anger to run a half marathon and get fit. most impoantly i use my experiences to heal and better myself and i will qualify as a solicitor and master of law later this year. 
i want to do a lot more to help others as i get stronger with the qualifications i have achieved. 
remember it is your healing journey and you need to do what’s right for you. don’t let anyone tell you what you should or should not be feeling, follow your own path and be your own guide 😘

text_retweet:
self-care isn't #bubblebaths and #facemasks, though those are examples of techniques you can use. #selfcare is an attitude shift, a conversation shift in your head. 
the old you would wake up with lists in your head of all the things you need to accomplish. 
the new you is practicing waking up with lists of all the ways you are going to support yourself throughout the day. 
the new you stops to ask: what do i need? 
what do i want? 
several times a day, as you work towards a mindset shift that brings balance between what you do for others and what you do for yourself. 
that's #selfcare and it doesn't cost you anything. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
⚠️ trigger warning: delicate subject and long post ⚠️ (1 of 2 or 3)
☆
we all want & need to be loved.
everyone's heard of #metoo. but no one has discussed the issues involved.
•
because, primarily men, abused primarily girls and young women, those women then thought that guys want sex. so that's what they did/ do with every man.
☆
can you see the problem?
•
guys brain's are wired different to women. guys want love too. but they see sex & love as separate. whereas women see it as the same thing. •
those women have got *stuck* in a cycle, wanting love, but not knowing how to get it (& by thinking that they need to give sex in order to get love...which, simply, just isn't true).
•
we get & receive love by forming healthy relationships over a period of time. building relationships. caring about each other. it's based on friendship. give & take. social skills. it takes time to build a loving relationship (years, not weeks/ months). both parties must be on the same page& want the same things in life (which should be established at the start).
☆
it affects billions of people all over the world. it affects men's ability to have loving relationships, as much as women's. it's our whole society.
☆

text: this is tarana burke! back in 1997 she sat across from a 13-year-old girl and listened to her experience of sexual abuse. the story left ms. burke speechless. she realized that she didn’t know what to say or how to help her. ten years later she created the organization just be incorporated which is an organization that works to help victims of sexual harassment and assault. the name of the movement this inspired? me too. despite the credit given alyssa milano for popularizing #metoo it was actually originally coined by tarana burke. it was pointed out by many black women that tarana had been working tirelessly to help victims but she had been largely ignored by white feminists. shocker. april reign, the woman who started #oscarssowhite said “white women have not been as supportive as they could have been of women of color when they experience targeted abuse and harassment,” using the espn anchor jemele hill and actress leslie jones as examples. she explained that this was the time for everyone to realize that the only way feminism will work is if it is intersectional. tarana was afraid her life work was about to be co-opted but the quick response by social media made sure that didn’t happen. we cannot imagine going back to a world before #metoo changed everything. and because of tarana burke we don’t have to. thank you, tarana.
name: Welcome To My Vagina!

text:
no matter how dark your world may seem
no matter how much concrete the world dumps on you
no matter how bad the storm
you will rise
through the cracks
of infinity despair
you will rise
through the bloodiest wars
you will rise
unbreakable, every ding or bent or even broken bones will only make you stronger
and you will rise!
my beautiful flower
you don’t even know how strong you are
how deep your roots
how full of love your soul and heart

i love you infinitely @halfway.dead_

text:
365 .
part 3 .

in october i filmed for wow women of wrestling television series .

later in the month i returned to vegas to work with my teams there and visit mom again. .

end of october our team goes into nation qualification doing over 160,000 in sales that month. .

november i head to palm desert for our area manager retreat. .

jacob returns home for thanksgiving, our team finishes our month with over 191,000 in sales. .

december i get down to my fighting weight of 110 lbs .

jacob returns home for christmas .

end of december our team finishes nation qualification along side my arbonne twin esmie with time to spare.  we dub ourselves the glow nation. .

in january our teams starts coaching over 147 detoxers on our 30 days to healthy living program. .

jacob and i are flown to maui compliments of arbonne and i attend my first ever nvp leadership retreat .

later in jan i’m back in vegas to work with our teams there and visit my mom again. .

in february kinga and i fly back in poland to celebrate marta’s region promotion and to give her the keys to her brand new white mercedes. .

you can call me an overachiever but i’d rather you call me an overcomer. .

i believe that sometimes you have to get knocked down lower than you've ever been, to stand up taller than you than you ever were. .

i’m not done honoring mike, i know i can’t bring him back but what i wanted to do more than anything was to make him proud. .

he always worried about everyone he loved and i know that seeing the impact his death made had to be just as hard on him as it was for all of us. .

i wanted this year to become something we could all grow from instead of something that destroyed us. .

i hope you felt the same way.
name: Little Egypt

part 3 .

in october i filmed for wow women of wrestling television series .

later in the month i returned to vegas to work with my teams there and visit mom again. .

november i head to palm desert for our area manager retreat. .

jacob returns home for thanksgiving, our team finishes our month with over 191,000 in sales. .

december i get down to my fighting weight of 110 lbs .

jacob returns home for christmas .

end of december our team finishes nation qualification along side my arbonne twin esmie with time to spare.  we dub ourselves the glow nation. .

in january our teams starts coaching over 147 detoxers on our 30 days to healthy living program. .

jacob and i are flown to maui compliments of arbonne and i attend my first ever nvp leadership retreat .

later in jan i’m back in vegas to work with our teams there and visit my mom again. .

in february kinga and i fly back in poland to celebrate marta’s region promotion and to give her the keys to her brand new white mercedes. .

you can call me an overachiever but i’d rather you call me an overcomer. .

i believe that sometimes you have to get knocked down lower than you have ever been, to stand up taller than you than you ever were. .

i’m not done honoring mike, i know i can’t bring him back but what i wanted to do more than anything was to make him proud. .

he always worried about everyone he loved and i know that seeing the impact his death made had to be just as hard on him as it was for all of us. .

365 .
pa 3 .

in october i filmed for wow women of wrestling television series .

later in the month i returned to vegas to work with my teams there and visit mom again. .

end of october our team goes into nation qualification doing over 160,000 in sales that month. .

november i head to palm dese for our area manager retreat. .

jacob returns home for thanksgiving, our team finishes our month with over 191,000 in sales. .

december i get down to my fighting weight of 110 lbs .

jacob returns home for christmas .

end of december our team finishes nation qualification along side my arbonne twin esmie with time to spare.  we dub ourselves the glow nation. .

in january our teams stas coaching over 147 detoxers on our 30 days to healthy living program. .

jacob and i are flown to maui compliments of arbonne and i attend my first ever nvp leadership retreat .

later in jan i’m back in vegas to work with our teams there and visit my mom again. .

in february kinga and i fly back in poland to celebrate maa’s region promotion and to give her the keys to her brand new white mercedes. .

you can call me an overachiever but i’d rather you call me an overcomer. .

i believe that sometimes you have to get knocked down lower than you have ever been, to stand up taller than you than you ever were. .

i’m not done honoring mike, i know i can’t bring him back but what i wanted to do more than anything was to make him proud. .

he always worried about everyone he loved and i know that seeing the impact his death made had to be just as hard on him as it was for all of us. .

i wanted this year to become something we could all grow from instead of something that destroyed us. .

i hope you felt the same way.

text:
this weeks article, excepts below, click the link in the bio for full article on doctorlarry.com.

what are your thoughts on the gillette masculinity commercial and what it means to be a man? 
jan 13 of this year, the razor company gillette released a commercial titled “we believe: the best men can be” which has proven to be quite controversial. in response, edgard watches ceo and founder ilan srulovicz, produced their own ad on masculinity. i’ve got both of them here on this page for you to watch. i’m curious what you think.

after watching each video:

what is your gut reaction?

what message did you hear?

i’ll be honest, my intention with this post has evolved as i’ve dug into this issue. my initial reaction to the gillette was, “yes, spot on!” and to the egard take, “this, too, is powerful.” i wanted to use both videos to encourage a conversation on what it means to be your best, today’s gentleman–a strong, successful man of character, who treats everyone (especially women) with respect. *and does so, with style.

but, as the comments below attest, but many men absolutely hated the first ad, vowing to boycott gillette because of the it. sounds like we need to talk, so i’m going to start by listening. here’s some representative comments i have copied and pasted from the comments section of joe rogan’s podcast where he discussed it. “they’re trying to make parents suppress a young boys instinctual masculine traits and turn them into men that will cry at the end of watching titanic on the 5th viewing.” “this is nothing more than radical feminist ideology wrapped in the once pure metoo movement. they’ve hijacked and mutated the metoo movement.” “challenging men to be better is fine, but as soon as they use the #metoo movement as some sort of awakening for men. yep never buying another gillette product.﻿” “could you imagine a tampon commercial telling girls not to grow up to be materialistic, gossiping gold diggers.?﻿” for full article, click the link in the bio.

#masculinity #gillette #egard #gentleman #doctor #yourbest

text:
maybe i am a feminist and a person who thrives in female company, solidarity and partnership because of something that happened in my family, or something that was ingrained in me at a young age. maybe i blame society too much and i judge men too harshly. that’s what (disclaimer: i am for normalizing therapy and i also think everyone should do it at least for a while) my therapist suggested today. or maybe, i am a woman and i know for a fact i am privileged because i have only experienced harassment and micro aggressions from men, while i listen to other women’s stories. but you know what? i don’t really care about why. i am a feminist and i will always be one. feminism affects me personally, but i will always stand for the oppressed and learn how to be a better ally for the unprivileged. i don’t care why. (i apologize for using gendered language, and i also would like to point out that while i have that uterus print in my wall my feminism is 100% inclusionary)
.
.

text:
survivors of sexual violence are often asked why they didn’t try fight back. when we are faced with danger our bodies automatically respond-we go into survival mode. for example our hearts might begin to beat faster, we may breathe faster and harder and our muscles may tense up. 
common reactions to sexual violence are to ‘freeze’, ’flop’ or ‘befriend’, sexual violence is about power and control. perpetrators are often ‘trusted’ people in our lives, stronger than us or have a form of control over us. survivors explain that they felt frozen with fear or unable to control their bodies,  others try to be kind, friendly and polite to potential attackers thinking this may stop them from assaulting them. 
please watch this video for more information on what not to say to a survivor of sexual assault: ‘things not to say to someone who's been sexually assaulted’ made by bbc on youtube.
.
.
.

text:
yhteiskunnalta vaaditaan koko ajan enemmän sukupuolten tasa-arvon suhteen.
lisäksi monet ovat sitä mieltä että ulkonäköasioista on tullut liian tärkeää.

kysyn, eikö me voida olla fiksummin?

voimmeko alkaa toteuttaa terveempiä arvoja myös käytännössä?

sopisiko tämä myös medialle?

onko sinusta tässä uutisessa mitään pielessä?

sen viesti on, että pitää näyttää hyvältä.
uutinen viittaa erityisesti naisiin.
näyttääkseen hyvältä, naisella lähtökohtaisesti tulee olla suuret rinnat?
ja ilmeisesti mielellään näkyvillä.

koska #metoo - kampanjan rinnalle tulee #mediatoo - kampanja?

koska alamme vaatia myös heiltä riman nostamista.

minusta jokaisen seksistisen uutisen voisi samalla tavalla kyseenalaistaa, mitä #metoo on julkisesti tehnyt.

#metoo #mediatoo #tasaarvo

🌚позаботьтесь о контенте

основа успеха в instagram — интересные фотографии, поэтому грамотно работайте с контентом, который предлагаете своим подписчикам.

найдите свою нишу. природные пейзажи, архитектура, портреты, натюрморты — делитесь снимками своего любимого жанра, и люди почувствуют ваше неравнодушное отношение к этой теме.
🌚 редактируйте снимки правильно

не стоит накладывать на фотографию десятки фильтров. определитесь с основной программой для редактирования и парой приложений-спутников. многие инструменты для обработки фотографий вы также найдёте в instagram. помните, что иногда лучше вообще отказаться от эффектов и передать снимок в максимально первозданном виде. редактирование фотографий должно лишь подчеркивать ваш замысел, но никак не заменять его.
🌚 отмечайте геолокации

пользователи instagram совершают поиск не только по хештегам, но и по интересным местам. не стоит бояться слежки спецслужб: они и так всё про вас знают.

text: “choose your hard” 🤔 i’ve heard #daveramsey say it: struggling to pay bills because you’re in debt vs working extra to pay it off 💵 i’ve heard #fitness influencers say it: diet and exercise is hard vs dealing with difficult health problems later on 🏃🏻‍♀️ and i’ve heard myself say it: stay in bed until 12 on a saturday feeling sorry for myself vs putting myself out there and choosing happiness! ☀️ now that i’m free from a controlling alcoholic, i feel energized to choose to make good, healthy food, to choose to do my hair and put on jewelry for work, i get to choose what i do in my free time instead of feeling sorry for myself and like i’m “behind” from where i “should be” by age 25 because of the choices i made in the past. i choose happiness 🦋 in the smallest ways no matter how “lame” or “boring” it may seem—walking the dog, volunteering, reading a book, cleaning the house, trying new recipes, etc! 😊 we were created to be stewards of this earth so it is time to make the right choices! 🙏 #sorrynotsorry #inspo #selflove #happiness #narcissist #narc #narcissisticabuse #alcoholabuse #alcoholics #metoo #weareher #emotionalabuse #mentalabuse #kingofexcuses #excuses #getout #alanon #poodle #poodlesofinstagram #doodlesofinstagram #forgiveness #freedom

text:
join us on april 4-6 for the 2019 primerus defense institute convocation in boca raton, florida! this outstanding educational program will feature thought leaders, experienced insurance coverage and defense attorneys, risk managers, and in-house counsel who will share their extensive knowledge related to challenges facing companies in today's marketplace and help you excel in your role as a strategic decision maker for your company. topics include: ➡️ changing times & the role of diversity and inclusiveness, succession planning, and client transparency
➡️ interpreting the new restatement of liability insurance
➡️ how tech risks impact representation of clients – the gdpr, statutory laws and regulatory landscape of privacy law
➡️ staying compliant with employment law and #metoo movement
➡️ ai – we are watching you
➡️ tech dynamics – staying ahead of the times

if you are interested in attending, please contact katie bundyra at kbundyra@primerus.com.

text:
music is not the only medium through which womxn’s voices will be featured on march 8th! art share l.a. is proud to present female gaze, an opening art reception happening alongside femme frequencies showcasing the work of 19 los angeles based artists. join us on friday, march 8, 2019 for an opening reception in the main gallery from 7 - 10pm.
.
featuring work from:
sarah gail armstrong, lara solanki brennan, claudia cogo, kitty davies, eliza day-green, luka fisher, june harley, caroline heer, marina heintze, alexis hunley, maura latty, kyra leah, babsi loisch, paloma montoya, amanda sade, tslil tsemet, roni weiss, anna wong-nelson, moy young
.
what is the female gaze? the male gaze is a term coined by feminist film theorist laura mulvey, representing the viewpoint of the male viewer, character, or creator in placing women to be objectified and viewed as spectacles — unable to dismiss or return the same gaze towards those male counterparts. mulvey’s term can be applied to any artistic form, from film and music to fine art and performance art.
.
under our current administration, and in the #metoo and time’s up era, what does this mean for how art is made and exhibited, by whom and for what audience? do we recognize this male gaze, reject it, change it, dissolve it? does it even still exist as a binary gender-based perspective, or has it evolved to signify any imbalance of power and agency? who defines the term, the viewer, or the viewed?
.
art share l.a.’s female gaze presents our experience as females, femme-identifying, non-binary, and ally communities in 2019 by staging a public forum for an on ongoing dialogue. what does the world look like through our gaze? and how that inevitably influences our creative practice.
.
